617  #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
618      static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyCode_New(int a, int p, int k, int l, int s, int f,
619                                                      PyObject *code, PyObject *c, PyObject* n, PyObject *v,
620                                                      PyObject *fv, PyObject *cell, PyObject* fn,
621                                                      PyObject *name, int fline, PyObject *lnos) {
622          PyObject *exception_table = NULL;
623          PyObject *types_module=NULL, *code_type=NULL, *result=NULL;
624          #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX < 0x030B0000
625          PyObject *version_info;
626          PyObject *py_minor_version = NULL;
627          #endif
628          long minor_version = 0;
629          PyObject *type, *value, *traceback;
630          PyErr_Fetch(&type, &value, &traceback);
631          #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B0000
632          minor_version = 11;
633          #else
634          if (!(version_info = PySys_GetObject("version_info"))) goto end;
635          if (!(py_minor_version = PySequence_GetItem(version_info, 1))) goto end;
636          minor_version = PyLong_AsLong(py_minor_version);
637          Py_DECREF(py_minor_version);
638          if (minor_version == -1 && PyErr_Occurred()) goto end;
639          #endif
640          if (!(types_module = PyImport_ImportModule("types"))) goto end;
641          if (!(code_type = PyObject_GetAttrString(types_module, "CodeType"))) goto end;
642          if (minor_version <= 7) {
643              (void)p;
644              result = PyObject_CallFunction(code_type, "iiiiiOOOOOOiOO", a, k, l, s, f, code,
645                            c, n, v, fn, name, fline, lnos, fv, cell);
646          } else if (minor_version <= 10) {
647              result = PyObject_CallFunction(code_type, "iiiiiiOOOOOOiOO", a,p, k, l, s, f, code,
648                            c, n, v, fn, name, fline, lnos, fv, cell);
649          } else {
650              if (!(exception_table = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(NULL, 0))) goto end;
651              result = PyObject_CallFunction(code_type, "iiiiiiOOOOOOOiOO", a,p, k, l, s, f, code,
652                            c, n, v, fn, name, name, fline, lnos, exception_table, fv, cell);
653          }
654      end:
655          Py_XDECREF(code_type);
656          Py_XDECREF(exception_table);
657          Py_XDECREF(types_module);
658          if (type) {
659              PyErr_Restore(type, value, traceback);
660          }
661          return result;
662      }

954  #define __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStrWithError  PyDict_GetItemWithError
955  #define __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr           PyDict_GetItem
956  #else
957  static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStrWithError(PyObject *dict, PyObject *name) {
958  #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
959      return PyDict_GetItem(dict, name);
960  #else
961      PyDictEntry *ep;
962      PyDictObject *mp = (PyDictObject*) dict;
963      long hash = ((PyStringObject *) name)->ob_shash;
964      assert(hash != -1);
965      ep = (mp->ma_lookup)(mp, name, hash);
966      if (ep == NULL) {
967          return NULL;
968      }
969      return ep->me_value;
970  #endif
971  }

1763         PyObject *tmp = (PyObject *) r;\

1765     } while (0)
1766 #define __Pyx_DECREF_SET(r, v) do {\
1767         PyObject *tmp = (PyObject *) r;\
1768         r = v; __Pyx_DECREF(tmp);\
1769     } while (0)
1770 #define __Pyx_CLEAR(r)    do { PyObject* tmp = ((PyObject*)(r)); r = NULL; __Pyx_DECREF(tmp);} while(0)
1771 #define __Pyx_XCLEAR(r)   do { if((r) != NULL) {PyObject* tmp = ((PyObject*)(r)); r = NULL; __Pyx_DECREF(tmp);}} while(0)

1902 #if CYTHON_USE_DICT_VERSIONS && CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
1903 #define __PYX_DICT_VERSION_INIT  ((PY_UINT64_T) -1)
1904 #define __PYX_GET_DICT_VERSION(dict)  (((PyDictObject*)(dict))->ma_version_tag)
1905 #define __PYX_UPDATE_DICT_CACHE(dict, value, cache_var, version_var)\
1906     (version_var) = __PYX_GET_DICT_VERSION(dict);\
1907     (cache_var) = (value);
1908 #define __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(VAR, DICT, LOOKUP) {\
1909     static PY_UINT64_T __pyx_dict_version = 0;\
1910     static PyObject *__pyx_dict_cached_value = NULL;\
1911     if (likely(__PYX_GET_DICT_VERSION(DICT) == __pyx_dict_version)) {\
1912         (VAR) = __pyx_dict_cached_value;\
1913     } else {\
1914         (VAR) = __pyx_dict_cached_value = (LOOKUP);\
1915         __pyx_dict_version = __PYX_GET_DICT_VERSION(DICT);\
1916     }\
1917 }
1918 static CYTHON_INLINE PY_UINT64_T __Pyx_get_tp_dict_version(PyObject *obj);
1919 static CYTHON_INLINE PY_UINT64_T __Pyx_get_object_dict_version(PyObject *obj);
1920 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_object_dict_version_matches(PyObject* obj, PY_UINT64_T tp_dict_version, PY_UINT64_T obj_dict_version);
1921 #else
1922 #define __PYX_GET_DICT_VERSION(dict)  (0)
1923 #define __PYX_UPDATE_DICT_CACHE(dict, value, cache_var, version_var)
1924 #define __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(VAR, DICT, LOOKUP)  (VAR) = (LOOKUP);

1999 /* AssertionsEnabled.proto */
2000 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x02070600 && !defined(Py_OptimizeFlag)
2001   #define __Pyx_init_assertions_enabled()  (0)
2002   #define __pyx_assertions_enabled()  (1)
2003 #elif CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API  ||  (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C0000)
2004   static int __pyx_assertions_enabled_flag;
2005   #define __pyx_assertions_enabled() (__pyx_assertions_enabled_flag)
2006   static int __Pyx_init_assertions_enabled(void) {
2007     PyObject *builtins, *debug, *debug_str;
2008     int flag;
2009     builtins = PyEval_GetBuiltins();
2010     if (!builtins) goto bad;
2011     debug_str = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize("__debug__", 9);
2012     if (!debug_str) goto bad;
2013     debug = PyObject_GetItem(builtins, debug_str);
2014     Py_DECREF(debug_str);
2015     if (!debug) goto bad;
2016     flag = PyObject_IsTrue(debug);
2017     Py_DECREF(debug);
2018     if (flag == -1) goto bad;
2019     __pyx_assertions_enabled_flag = flag;
2020     return 0;
2021   bad:
2022     __pyx_assertions_enabled_flag = 1;
2023     return -1;
2024   }
2025 #else
2026   #define __Pyx_init_assertions_enabled()  (0)
2027   #define __pyx_assertions_enabled()  (!Py_OptimizeFlag)
2028 #endif

20731 /* PyErrExceptionMatches */
20732 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
20733 static int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
20734     Py_ssize_t i, n;
20735     n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
20736 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
20737     for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
20738         if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
20739     }
20740 #endif
20741     for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
20742         if (__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i))) return 1;
20743     }
20744     return 0;
20745 }
20746 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesInState(PyThreadState* tstate, PyObject* err) {
20747     int result;
20748     PyObject *exc_type;
20749 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A6
20750     PyObject *current_exception = tstate->current_exception;
20751     if (unlikely(!current_exception)) return 0;
20752     exc_type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(current_exception);
20753     if (exc_type == err) return 1;
20754 #else
20755     exc_type = tstate->curexc_type;
20756     if (exc_type == err) return 1;
20757     if (unlikely(!exc_type)) return 0;
20758 #endif
20759     #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
20760     Py_INCREF(exc_type);
20761     #endif
20762     if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(err))) {
20763         result = __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(exc_type, err);
20764     } else {
20765         result = __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, err);
20766     }
20767     #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
20768     Py_DECREF(exc_type);
20769     #endif
20770     return result;
20771 }

20774 /* PyErrFetchRestore */
20775 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
20776 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb) {
20777 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A6
20778     PyObject *tmp_value;
20779     assert(type == NULL || (value != NULL && type == (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value)));
20780     if (value) {
20781         #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON

20787     tstate->current_exception = value;
20788     Py_XDECREF(tmp_value);

20791 #else

20795     tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
20796     tstate->curexc_type = type;
20797     tstate->curexc_value = value;
20798     tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
20799     Py_XDECREF(tmp_type);

20801     Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);

20820         #endif
20821     }
20822 #else
20823     *type = tstate->curexc_type;
20824     *value = tstate->curexc_value;
20825     *tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
20826     tstate->curexc_type = 0;
20827     tstate->curexc_value = 0;

20927 /* BytesEquals */
20928 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyBytes_Equals(PyObject* s1, PyObject* s2, int equals) {
20929 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
20930     return PyObject_RichCompareBool(s1, s2, equals);
20931 #else
20932     if (s1 == s2) {
20933         return (equals == Py_EQ);
20934     } else if (PyBytes_CheckExact(s1) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s2)) {
20935         const char *ps1, *ps2;
20936         Py_ssize_t length = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(s1);
20937         if (length != PyBytes_GET_SIZE(s2))
20938             return (equals == Py_NE);
20939         ps1 = PyBytes_AS_STRING(s1);
20940         ps2 = PyBytes_AS_STRING(s2);
20941         if (ps1[0] != ps2[0]) {
20942             return (equals == Py_NE);
20943         } else if (length == 1) {
20944             return (equals == Py_EQ);
20945         } else {
20946             int result;
20947 #if CYTHON_USE_UNICODE_INTERNALS && (PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030B0000)
20948             Py_hash_t hash1, hash2;
20949             hash1 = ((PyBytesObject*)s1)->ob_shash;
20950             hash2 = ((PyBytesObject*)s2)->ob_shash;
20951             if (hash1 != hash2 && hash1 != -1 && hash2 != -1) {
20952                 return (equals == Py_NE);
20953             }
20954 #endif
20955             result = memcmp(ps1, ps2, (size_t)length);
20956             return (equals == Py_EQ) ? (result == 0) : (result != 0);
20957         }
20958     } else if ((s1 == Py_None) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s2)) {
20959         return (equals == Py_NE);
20960     } else if ((s2 == Py_None) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s1)) {
20961         return (equals == Py_NE);
20962     } else {
20963         int result;
20964         PyObject* py_result = PyObject_RichCompare(s1, s2, equals);
20965         if (!py_result)
20966             return -1;
20967         result = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(py_result);
20968         Py_DECREF(py_result);
20969         return result;
20970     }
20971 #endif
20972 }

20974 /* UnicodeEquals */
20975 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyUnicode_Equals(PyObject* s1, PyObject* s2, int equals) {
20976 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
20977     return PyObject_RichCompareBool(s1, s2, equals);
20978 #else
20979 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
20980     PyObject* owned_ref = NULL;
20981 #endif
20982     int s1_is_unicode, s2_is_unicode;
20983     if (s1 == s2) {
20984         goto return_eq;
20985     }
20986     s1_is_unicode = PyUnicode_CheckExact(s1);
20987     s2_is_unicode = PyUnicode_CheckExact(s2);
20988 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
20989     if ((s1_is_unicode & (!s2_is_unicode)) && PyString_CheckExact(s2)) {
20990         owned_ref = PyUnicode_FromObject(s2);
20991         if (unlikely(!owned_ref))
20992             return -1;
20993         s2 = owned_ref;
20994         s2_is_unicode = 1;
20995     } else if ((s2_is_unicode & (!s1_is_unicode)) && PyString_CheckExact(s1)) {
20996         owned_ref = PyUnicode_FromObject(s1);
20997         if (unlikely(!owned_ref))
20998             return -1;
20999         s1 = owned_ref;
21000         s1_is_unicode = 1;
21001     } else if (((!s2_is_unicode) & (!s1_is_unicode))) {
21002         return __Pyx_PyBytes_Equals(s1, s2, equals);
21003     }
21004 #endif
21005     if (s1_is_unicode & s2_is_unicode) {
21006         Py_ssize_t length;
21007         int kind;
21008         void *data1, *data2;
21009         if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(s1) < 0) || unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(s2) < 0))
21010             return -1;
21011         length = __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(s1);
21012         if (length != __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(s2)) {
21013             goto return_ne;
21014         }
21015 #if CYTHON_USE_UNICODE_INTERNALS
21016         {
21017             Py_hash_t hash1, hash2;
21018         #if CYTHON_PEP393_ENABLED
21019             hash1 = ((PyASCIIObject*)s1)->hash;
21020             hash2 = ((PyASCIIObject*)s2)->hash;
21021         #else
21022             hash1 = ((PyUnicodeObject*)s1)->hash;
21023             hash2 = ((PyUnicodeObject*)s2)->hash;
21024         #endif
21025             if (hash1 != hash2 && hash1 != -1 && hash2 != -1) {
21026                 goto return_ne;
21027             }
21028         }
21029 #endif
21030         kind = __Pyx_PyUnicode_KIND(s1);
21031         if (kind != __Pyx_PyUnicode_KIND(s2)) {
21032             goto return_ne;
21033         }
21034         data1 = __Pyx_PyUnicode_DATA(s1);
21035         data2 = __Pyx_PyUnicode_DATA(s2);
21036         if (__Pyx_PyUnicode_READ(kind, data1, 0) != __Pyx_PyUnicode_READ(kind, data2, 0)) {
21037             goto return_ne;
21038         } else if (length == 1) {
21039             goto return_eq;
21040         } else {
21041             int result = memcmp(data1, data2, (size_t)(length * kind));
21042             #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21043             Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
21044             #endif
21045             return (equals == Py_EQ) ? (result == 0) : (result != 0);
21046         }
21047     } else if ((s1 == Py_None) & s2_is_unicode) {
21048         goto return_ne;
21049     } else if ((s2 == Py_None) & s1_is_unicode) {
21050         goto return_ne;
21051     } else {
21052         int result;
21053         PyObject* py_result = PyObject_RichCompare(s1, s2, equals);
21054         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21055         Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
21056         #endif
21057         if (!py_result)
21058             return -1;
21059         result = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(py_result);
21060         Py_DECREF(py_result);
21061         return result;
21062     }
21063 return_eq:
21064     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21065     Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
21066     #endif
21067     return (equals == Py_EQ);
21068 return_ne:
21069     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21070     Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
21071     #endif
21072     return (equals == Py_NE);
21073 #endif
21074 }

21186 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(PyCodeObject *co, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t na,
21187                                                PyObject *globals) {
21188     PyFrameObject *f;
21189     PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
21190     PyObject **fastlocals;
21191     Py_ssize_t i;
21192     PyObject *result;
21193     assert(globals != NULL);
21194     /* XXX Perhaps we should create a specialized 
21195        PyFrame_New() that doesn't take locals, but does 
21196        take builtins without sanity checking them. 
21197        */
21198     assert(tstate != NULL);
21199     f = PyFrame_New(tstate, co, globals, NULL);
21200     if (f == NULL) {
21201         return NULL;
21202     }
21203     fastlocals = __Pyx_PyFrame_GetLocalsplus(f);
21204     for (i = 0; i < na; i++) {
21205         Py_INCREF(*args);
21206         fastlocals[i] = *args++;
21207     }
21208     result = PyEval_EvalFrameEx(f,0);
21209     ++tstate->recursion_depth;
21210     Py_DECREF(f);
21211     --tstate->recursion_depth;
21212     return result;
21213 }
21214 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
21215     PyCodeObject *co = (PyCodeObject *)PyFunction_GET_CODE(func);
21216     PyObject *globals = PyFunction_GET_GLOBALS(func);
21217     PyObject *argdefs = PyFunction_GET_DEFAULTS(func);
21218     PyObject *closure;
21219 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
21220     PyObject *kwdefs;
21221 #endif
21222     PyObject *kwtuple, **k;
21223     PyObject **d;
21224     Py_ssize_t nd;
21225     Py_ssize_t nk;
21226     PyObject *result;
21227     assert(kwargs == NULL || PyDict_Check(kwargs));
21228     nk = kwargs ? PyDict_Size(kwargs) : 0;
21229     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21230     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object"))) {
21231         return NULL;
21232     }
21233     #else
21234     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall(" while calling a Python object"))) {
21235         return NULL;
21236     }
21237     #endif
21238     if (
21239 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
21240             co->co_kwonlyargcount == 0 &&
21241 #endif
21242             likely(kwargs == NULL || nk == 0) &&
21243             co->co_flags == (CO_OPTIMIZED | CO_NEWLOCALS | CO_NOFREE)) {
21244         if (argdefs == NULL && co->co_argcount == nargs) {
21245             result = __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, nargs, globals);
21246             goto done;
21247         }
21248         else if (nargs == 0 && argdefs != NULL
21249                  && co->co_argcount == Py_SIZE(argdefs)) {
21250             /* function called with no arguments, but all parameters have 
21251                a default value: use default values as arguments .*/
21252             args = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
21253             result =__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, Py_SIZE(argdefs), globals);
21254             goto done;
21255         }
21256     }
21257     if (kwargs != NULL) {
21258         Py_ssize_t pos, i;
21259         kwtuple = PyTuple_New(2 * nk);
21260         if (kwtuple == NULL) {
21261             result = NULL;
21262             goto done;
21263         }
21264         k = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kwtuple, 0);
21265         pos = i = 0;
21266         while (PyDict_Next(kwargs, &pos, &k[i], &k[i+1])) {
21267             Py_INCREF(k[i]);
21268             Py_INCREF(k[i+1]);
21269             i += 2;
21270         }
21271         nk = i / 2;
21272     }
21273     else {
21274         kwtuple = NULL;
21275         k = NULL;
21276     }
21277     closure = PyFunction_GET_CLOSURE(func);
21278 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
21279     kwdefs = PyFunction_GET_KW_DEFAULTS(func);
21280 #endif
21281     if (argdefs != NULL) {
21282         d = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
21283         nd = Py_SIZE(argdefs);
21284     }
21285     else {
21286         d = NULL;
21287         nd = 0;
21288     }
21289 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
21290     result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx((PyObject*)co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
21291                                args, (int)nargs,
21292                                k, (int)nk,
21293                                d, (int)nd, kwdefs, closure);
21294 #else
21295     result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx(co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
21296                                args, (int)nargs,
21297                                k, (int)nk,
21298                                d, (int)nd, closure);
21299 #endif
21300     Py_XDECREF(kwtuple);
21301 done:
21302     Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
21303     return result;
21304 }
21305 #endif

21307 /* PyObjectCall */
21308 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
21309 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_Call(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
21310     PyObject *result;
21311     ternaryfunc call = Py_TYPE(func)->tp_call;
21312     if (unlikely(!call))
21313         return PyObject_Call(func, arg, kw);
21314     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21315     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
21316         return NULL;
21317     #else
21318     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall(" while calling a Python object")))
21319         return NULL;
21320     #endif
21321     result = (*call)(func, arg, kw);
21322     Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
21323     if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
21324         PyErr_SetString(
21325             PyExc_SystemError,
21326             "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
21327     }
21328     return result;
21329 }
21330 #endif

21333 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
21334 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
21335     PyObject *self, *result;
21336     PyCFunction cfunc;
21337     cfunc = __Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(func);
21338     self = __Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_GET_SELF(func);
21339     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21340     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
21341         return NULL;
21342     #else
21343     if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall(" while calling a Python object")))
21344         return NULL;
21345     #endif
21346     result = cfunc(self, arg);
21347     Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
21348     if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
21349         PyErr_SetString(
21350             PyExc_SystemError,
21351             "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
21352     }
21353     return result;

21357 /* PyObjectFastCall */
21358 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03090000 || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
21359 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_FastCall_fallback(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, size_t nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
21360     PyObject *argstuple;
21361     PyObject *result = 0;
21362     size_t i;
21363     argstuple = PyTuple_New((Py_ssize_t)nargs);
21364     if (unlikely(!argstuple)) return NULL;
21365     for (i = 0; i < nargs; i++) {
21366         Py_INCREF(args[i]);
21367         if (__Pyx_PyTuple_SET_ITEM(argstuple, (Py_ssize_t)i, args[i]) < 0) goto bad;
21368     }
21369     result = __Pyx_PyObject_Call(func, argstuple, kwargs);
21370   bad:
21371     Py_DECREF(argstuple);
21372     return result;
21373 }
21374 #endif
21375 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, size_t _nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
21376     Py_ssize_t nargs = __Pyx_PyVectorcall_NARGS(_nargs);
21377 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
21378     if (nargs == 0 && kwargs == NULL) {
21379         if (__Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_Check(func) && likely( __Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func) & METH_NOARGS))
21380             return __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(func, NULL);
21381     }
21382     else if (nargs == 1 && kwargs == NULL) {
21383         if (__Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_Check(func) && likely( __Pyx_CyOrPyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func) & METH_O))
21384             return __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(func, args[0]);
21385     }
21386 #endif
21387     #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030800B1
21388     #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
21389     if (PyCFunction_Check(func)) {
21390         if (kwargs) {
21391             return _PyCFunction_FastCallDict(func, args, nargs, kwargs);
21392         } else {
21393             return _PyCFunction_FastCallKeywords(func, args, nargs, NULL);
21394         }
21395     }
21396     #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030700A1
21397     if (!kwargs && __Pyx_IS_TYPE(func, &PyMethodDescr_Type)) {
21398         return _PyMethodDescr_FastCallKeywords(func, args, nargs, NULL);
21399     }
21400     #endif
21401     #endif
21402     #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
21403     if (PyFunction_Check(func)) {
21404         return __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallDict(func, args, nargs, kwargs);
21405     }
21406     #endif
21407     #endif
21408     if (kwargs == NULL) {
21409         #if CYTHON_VECTORCALL
21410         #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03090000
21411         vectorcallfunc f = _PyVectorcall_Function(func);
21412         #else
21413         vectorcallfunc f = PyVectorcall_Function(func);
21414         #endif
21415         if (f) {
21416             return f(func, args, (size_t)nargs, NULL);
21417         }
21418         #elif defined(__Pyx_CyFunction_USED) && CYTHON_BACKPORT_VECTORCALL
21419         if (__Pyx_CyFunction_CheckExact(func)) {
21420             __pyx_vectorcallfunc f = __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(func);
21421             if (f) return f(func, args, (size_t)nargs, NULL);
21422         }
21423         #endif
21424     }
21425     if (nargs == 0) {
21426         return __Pyx_PyObject_Call(func, __pyx_empty_tuple, kwargs);
21427     }
21428     #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x03090000 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
21429     return PyObject_VectorcallDict(func, args, (size_t)nargs, kwargs);
21430     #else
21431     return __Pyx_PyObject_FastCall_fallback(func, args, (size_t)nargs, kwargs);
21432     #endif
21433 }

21435 /* RaiseException */
21436 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21437 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb, PyObject *cause) {
21438     __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
21439     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(cause);
21440     Py_XINCREF(type);
21441     if (!value || value == Py_None)
21442         value = NULL;
21443     else
21444         Py_INCREF(value);
21445     if (!tb || tb == Py_None)
21446         tb = NULL;
21447     else {
21448         Py_INCREF(tb);
21449         if (!PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
21450             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21451                 "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
21452             goto raise_error;
21453         }
21454     }
21455     if (PyType_Check(type)) {
21456 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
21457         if (!value) {
21458             Py_INCREF(Py_None);
21459             value = Py_None;
21460         }
21461 #endif
21462         PyErr_NormalizeException(&type, &value, &tb);
21463     } else {
21464         if (value) {
21465             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21466                 "instance exception may not have a separate value");
21467             goto raise_error;
21468         }
21469         value = type;
21470         type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(type);
21471         Py_INCREF(type);
21472         if (!PyType_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject *)type, (PyTypeObject *)PyExc_BaseException)) {
21473             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21474                 "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
21475             goto raise_error;
21476         }
21477     }
21478     __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
21479     __Pyx_ErrRestore(type, value, tb);
21480     return;
21481 raise_error:
21482     Py_XDECREF(value);
21483     Py_XDECREF(type);
21484     Py_XDECREF(tb);
21485     return;
21486 }
21487 #else
21488 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb, PyObject *cause) {
21489     PyObject* owned_instance = NULL;
21490     if (tb == Py_None) {
21491         tb = 0;
21492     } else if (tb && !PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
21493         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21494             "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
21495         goto bad;
21496     }
21497     if (value == Py_None)
21498         value = 0;
21499     if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(type)) {
21500         if (value) {
21501             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21502                 "instance exception may not have a separate value");
21503             goto bad;
21504         }
21505         value = type;
21506         type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
21507     } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(type)) {
21508         PyObject *instance_class = NULL;
21509         if (value && PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
21510             instance_class = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
21511             if (instance_class != type) {
21512                 int is_subclass = PyObject_IsSubclass(instance_class, type);
21513                 if (!is_subclass) {
21514                     instance_class = NULL;
21515                 } else if (unlikely(is_subclass == -1)) {
21516                     goto bad;
21517                 } else {
21518                     type = instance_class;
21519                 }
21520             }
21521         }
21522         if (!instance_class) {
21523             PyObject *args;
21524             if (!value)
21525                 args = PyTuple_New(0);
21526             else if (PyTuple_Check(value)) {
21527                 Py_INCREF(value);
21528                 args = value;
21529             } else
21530                 args = PyTuple_Pack(1, value);
21531             if (!args)
21532                 goto bad;
21533             owned_instance = PyObject_Call(type, args, NULL);
21534             Py_DECREF(args);
21535             if (!owned_instance)
21536                 goto bad;
21537             value = owned_instance;
21538             if (!PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
21539                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
21540                              "calling %R should have returned an instance of "
21541                              "BaseException, not %R",
21542                              type, Py_TYPE(value));
21543                 goto bad;
21544             }
21545         }
21546     } else {
21547         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21548             "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
21549         goto bad;
21550     }
21551     if (cause) {
21552         PyObject *fixed_cause;
21553         if (cause == Py_None) {
21554             fixed_cause = NULL;
21555         } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(cause)) {
21556             fixed_cause = PyObject_CallObject(cause, NULL);
21557             if (fixed_cause == NULL)
21558                 goto bad;
21559         } else if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(cause)) {
21560             fixed_cause = cause;
21561             Py_INCREF(fixed_cause);
21562         } else {
21563             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
21564                             "exception causes must derive from "
21565                             "BaseException");
21566             goto bad;
21567         }
21568         PyException_SetCause(value, fixed_cause);
21569     }
21570     PyErr_SetObject(type, value);
21571     if (tb) {
21572       #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A6
21573         PyException_SetTraceback(value, tb);
21574       #elif CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21575         PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
21576         PyObject* tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
21577         if (tb != tmp_tb) {
21578             Py_INCREF(tb);
21579             tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
21580             Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
21581         }
21582 #else
21583         PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
21584         PyErr_Fetch(&tmp_type, &tmp_value, &tmp_tb);
21585         Py_INCREF(tb);
21586         PyErr_Restore(tmp_type, tmp_value, tb);
21587         Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
21588 #endif
21589     }
21590 bad:
21591     Py_XDECREF(owned_instance);
21592     return;
21593 }
21594 #endif

21596 /* PyIntBinop */
21597 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
21598 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_AddObjC(PyObject *op1, PyObject *op2, long intval, int inplace, int zerodivision_check) {
21599     CYTHON_MAYBE_UNUSED_VAR(intval);
21600     CYTHON_MAYBE_UNUSED_VAR(inplace);
21601     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(zerodivision_check);
21602     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21603     if (likely(PyInt_CheckExact(op1))) {
21604         const long b = intval;
21605         long x;
21606         long a = PyInt_AS_LONG(op1);
21607         
21608             x = (long)((unsigned long)a + (unsigned long)b);
21609             if (likely((x^a) >= 0 || (x^b) >= 0))
21610                 return PyInt_FromLong(x);
21611             return PyLong_Type.tp_as_number->nb_add(op1, op2);
21612     }
21613     #endif
21614     #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
21615     if (likely(PyLong_CheckExact(op1))) {
21616         const long b = intval;
21617         long a, x;
21618 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21619         const PY_LONG_LONG llb = intval;
21620         PY_LONG_LONG lla, llx;
21621 #endif
21622         if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyLong_IsZero(op1))) {
21623             return __Pyx_NewRef(op2);
21624         }
21625         if (likely(__Pyx_PyLong_IsCompact(op1))) {
21626             a = __Pyx_PyLong_CompactValue(op1);
21627         } else {
21628             const digit* digits = __Pyx_PyLong_Digits(op1);
21629             const Py_ssize_t size = __Pyx_PyLong_SignedDigitCount(op1);
21630             switch (size) {
21631                 case -2:
21632                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21633                         a = -(long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21634                         break;
21635                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21636                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21637                         lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21638                         goto long_long;
21639                     #endif
21640                     }
21641                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21642                 case 2:
21643                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21644                         a = (long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21645                         break;
21646                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21647                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21648                         lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21649                         goto long_long;
21650                     #endif
21651                     }
21652                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21653                 case -3:
21654                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21655                         a = -(long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21656                         break;
21657                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21658                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21659                         lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21660                         goto long_long;
21661                     #endif
21662                     }
21663                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21664                 case 3:
21665                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21666                         a = (long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21667                         break;
21668                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21669                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21670                         lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21671                         goto long_long;
21672                     #endif
21673                     }
21674                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21675                 case -4:
21676                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21677                         a = -(long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21678                         break;
21679                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21680                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21681                         lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21682                         goto long_long;
21683                     #endif
21684                     }
21685                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21686                 case 4:
21687                     if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21688                         a = (long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
21689                         break;
21690                     #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21691                     } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
21692                         lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
21693                         goto long_long;
21694                     #endif
21695                     }
21696                     CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
21697                 default: return PyLong_Type.tp_as_number->nb_add(op1, op2);
21698             }
21699         }
21700                 x = a + b;
21701             return PyLong_FromLong(x);
21702 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
21703         long_long:
21704                 llx = lla + llb;
21705             return PyLong_FromLongLong(llx);
21706 #endif
21707         
21708         
21709     }
21710     #endif
21711     if (PyFloat_CheckExact(op1)) {
21712         const long b = intval;
21713 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
21714         double a = __pyx_PyFloat_AsDouble(op1);
21715 #else
21716         double a = PyFloat_AS_DOUBLE(op1);
21717 #endif
21718             double result;
21719             
21720             PyFPE_START_PROTECT("add", return NULL)
21721             result = ((double)a) + (double)b;
21722             PyFPE_END_PROTECT(result)
21723             return PyFloat_FromDouble(result);
21724     }
21725     return (inplace ? PyNumber_InPlaceAdd : PyNumber_Add)(op1, op2);
21726 }
21727 #endif
21728 
21729 /* SliceObject */
21730 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_GetSlice(PyObject* obj,
21731         Py_ssize_t cstart, Py_ssize_t cstop,
21732         PyObject** _py_start, PyObject** _py_stop, PyObject** _py_slice,
21733         int has_cstart, int has_cstop, int wraparound) {
21734     __Pyx_TypeName obj_type_name;
21735 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
21736     PyMappingMethods* mp;
21737 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
21738     PySequenceMethods* ms = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_sequence;
21739     if (likely(ms && ms->sq_slice)) {
21740         if (!has_cstart) {
21741             if (_py_start && (*_py_start != Py_None)) {
21742                 cstart = __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(*_py_start);
21743                 if ((cstart == (Py_ssize_t)-1) && PyErr_Occurred()) goto bad;
21744             } else
21745                 cstart = 0;
21746         }
21747         if (!has_cstop) {
21748             if (_py_stop && (*_py_stop != Py_None)) {
21749                 cstop = __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(*_py_stop);
21750                 if ((cstop == (Py_ssize_t)-1) && PyErr_Occurred()) goto bad;
21751             } else
21752                 cstop = PY_SSIZE_T_MAX;
21753         }
21754         if (wraparound && unlikely((cstart < 0) | (cstop < 0)) && likely(ms->sq_length)) {
21755             Py_ssize_t l = ms->sq_length(obj);
21756             if (likely(l >= 0)) {
21757                 if (cstop < 0) {
21758                     cstop += l;
21759                     if (cstop < 0) cstop = 0;
21760                 }
21761                 if (cstart < 0) {
21762                     cstart += l;
21763                     if (cstart < 0) cstart = 0;
21764                 }
21765             } else {
21766                 if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
21767                     goto bad;
21768                 PyErr_Clear();
21769             }
21770         }
21771         return ms->sq_slice(obj, cstart, cstop);
21772     }
21773 #else
21774     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(wraparound);
21775 #endif
21776     mp = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_mapping;
21777     if (likely(mp && mp->mp_subscript))
21778 #else
21779     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(wraparound);
21780 #endif
21781     {
21782         PyObject* result;
21783         PyObject *py_slice, *py_start, *py_stop;
21784         if (_py_slice) {
21785             py_slice = *_py_slice;
21786         } else {
21787             PyObject* owned_start = NULL;
21788             PyObject* owned_stop = NULL;
21789             if (_py_start) {
21790                 py_start = *_py_start;
21791             } else {
21792                 if (has_cstart) {
21793                     owned_start = py_start = PyInt_FromSsize_t(cstart);
21794                     if (unlikely(!py_start)) goto bad;
21795                 } else
21796                     py_start = Py_None;
21797             }
21798             if (_py_stop) {
21799                 py_stop = *_py_stop;
21800             } else {
21801                 if (has_cstop) {
21802                     owned_stop = py_stop = PyInt_FromSsize_t(cstop);
21803                     if (unlikely(!py_stop)) {
21804                         Py_XDECREF(owned_start);
21805                         goto bad;
21806                     }
21807                 } else
21808                     py_stop = Py_None;
21809             }
21810             py_slice = PySlice_New(py_start, py_stop, Py_None);
21811             Py_XDECREF(owned_start);
21812             Py_XDECREF(owned_stop);
21813             if (unlikely(!py_slice)) goto bad;
21814         }
21815 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
21816         result = mp->mp_subscript(obj, py_slice);
21817 #else
21818         result = PyObject_GetItem(obj, py_slice);
21819 #endif
21820         if (!_py_slice) {
21821             Py_DECREF(py_slice);
21822         }
21823         return result;
21824     }
21825     obj_type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(Py_TYPE(obj));
21826     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
21827         "'" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' object is unsliceable", obj_type_name);
21828     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(obj_type_name);
21829 bad:
21830     return NULL;
21831 }

21833 /* GetAttr3 */
21834 #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX < 0x030d00A1
21835 static PyObject *__Pyx_GetAttr3Default(PyObject *d) {
21836     __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
21837     __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
21838     if (unlikely(!__Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)))
21839         return NULL;
21840     __Pyx_PyErr_Clear();
21841     Py_INCREF(d);
21842     return d;
21843 }
21844 #endif
21845 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetAttr3(PyObject *o, PyObject *n, PyObject *d) {
21846     PyObject *r;
21847 #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030d00A1
21848     int res = PyObject_GetOptionalAttr(o, n, &r);
21849     return (res != 0) ? r : __Pyx_NewRef(d);
21850 #else
21851   #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
21852     if (likely(PyString_Check(n))) {
21853         r = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(o, n);
21854         if (unlikely(!r) && likely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
21855             r = __Pyx_NewRef(d);
21856         }
21857         return r;
21858     }
21859   #endif
21860     r = PyObject_GetAttr(o, n);
21861     return (likely(r)) ? r : __Pyx_GetAttr3Default(d);
21862 #endif
21863 }

21871 /* GetTopmostException */
21872 #if CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK && CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21873 static _PyErr_StackItem *
21874 __Pyx_PyErr_GetTopmostException(PyThreadState *tstate)
21875 {
21876     _PyErr_StackItem *exc_info = tstate->exc_info;
21877     while ((exc_info->exc_value == NULL || exc_info->exc_value == Py_None) &&
21878            exc_info->previous_item != NULL)
21879     {
21880         exc_info = exc_info->previous_item;
21881     }
21882     return exc_info;

21886 /* SaveResetException */
21887 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21888 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx__ExceptionSave(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb) {
21889   #if CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B00a4
21890     _PyErr_StackItem *exc_info = __Pyx_PyErr_GetTopmostException(tstate);

21908     Py_XINCREF(*type);
21909     Py_XINCREF(*value);
21910     Py_XINCREF(*tb);
21911   #else

21913     *value = tstate->exc_value;
21914     *tb = tstate->exc_traceback;
21915     Py_XINCREF(*type);
21916     Py_XINCREF(*value);
21917     Py_XINCREF(*tb);
21918   #endif
21919 }

21933     tmp_value = exc_info->exc_value;

21936     exc_info->exc_value = value;
21937     exc_info->exc_traceback = tb;
21938     #else

21940     tmp_value = tstate->exc_value;
21941     tmp_tb = tstate->exc_traceback;
21942     tstate->exc_type = type;
21943     tstate->exc_value = value;
21944     tstate->exc_traceback = tb;
21945     #endif

21953 /* GetException */
21954 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21955 static int __Pyx__GetException(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)
21956 #else
21957 static int __Pyx_GetException(PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)
21958 #endif
21959 {
21960     PyObject *local_type = NULL, *local_value, *local_tb = NULL;
21961 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21962     PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
21963   #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A6
21964     local_value = tstate->current_exception;
21965     tstate->current_exception = 0;
21966     if (likely(local_value)) {
21967         local_type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(local_value);
21968         Py_INCREF(local_type);
21969         local_tb = PyException_GetTraceback(local_value);
21970     }
21971   #else
21972     local_type = tstate->curexc_type;
21973     local_value = tstate->curexc_value;
21974     local_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
21975     tstate->curexc_type = 0;
21976     tstate->curexc_value = 0;
21977     tstate->curexc_traceback = 0;
21978   #endif
21979 #else
21980     PyErr_Fetch(&local_type, &local_value, &local_tb);
21981 #endif
21982     PyErr_NormalizeException(&local_type, &local_value, &local_tb);
21983 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A6
21984     if (unlikely(tstate->current_exception))
21985 #elif CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
21986     if (unlikely(tstate->curexc_type))
21987 #else
21988     if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred()))
21989 #endif
21990         goto bad;
21991     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
21992     if (local_tb) {
21993         if (unlikely(PyException_SetTraceback(local_value, local_tb) < 0))
21994             goto bad;
21995     }
21996     #endif
21997     Py_XINCREF(local_tb);
21998     Py_XINCREF(local_type);
21999     Py_XINCREF(local_value);
22000     *type = local_type;
22001     *value = local_value;
22002     *tb = local_tb;
22003 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
22004     #if CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK
22005     {
22006         _PyErr_StackItem *exc_info = tstate->exc_info;
22007       #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B00a4
22008         tmp_value = exc_info->exc_value;
22009         exc_info->exc_value = local_value;
22010         tmp_type = NULL;
22011         tmp_tb = NULL;
22012         Py_XDECREF(local_type);
22013         Py_XDECREF(local_tb);
22014       #else
22015         tmp_type = exc_info->exc_type;
22016         tmp_value = exc_info->exc_value;
22017         tmp_tb = exc_info->exc_traceback;
22018         exc_info->exc_type = local_type;
22019         exc_info->exc_value = local_value;
22020         exc_info->exc_traceback = local_tb;
22021       #endif
22022     }
22023     #else
22024     tmp_type = tstate->exc_type;
22025     tmp_value = tstate->exc_value;
22026     tmp_tb = tstate->exc_traceback;
22027     tstate->exc_type = local_type;
22028     tstate->exc_value = local_value;
22029     tstate->exc_traceback = local_tb;
22030     #endif
22031     Py_XDECREF(tmp_type);
22032     Py_XDECREF(tmp_value);
22033     Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
22034 #else
22035     PyErr_SetExcInfo(local_type, local_value, local_tb);
22036 #endif
22037     return 0;
22038 bad:
22039     *type = 0;
22040     *value = 0;
22041     *tb = 0;
22042     Py_XDECREF(local_type);
22043     Py_XDECREF(local_value);
22044     Py_XDECREF(local_tb);
22045     return -1;
22046 }

22048 /* PyObjectLookupSpecial */
22049 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP && CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
22050 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx__PyObject_LookupSpecial(PyObject* obj, PyObject* attr_name, int with_error) {
22051     PyObject *res;
22052     PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(obj);
22053 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22054     if (unlikely(PyInstance_Check(obj)))

22056 #endif

22059         descrgetfunc f = Py_TYPE(res)->tp_descr_get;

22063             res = f(res, obj, (PyObject *)tp);
22064         }
22065     } else if (with_error) {
22066         PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_AttributeError, attr_name);
22067     }
22068     return res;
22069 }

22111 /* SwapException */
22112 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
22113 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx__ExceptionSwap(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb) {
22114     PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
22115   #if CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B00a4

22126         Py_INCREF(tmp_type);
22127         #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
22128         tmp_tb = ((PyBaseExceptionObject*) tmp_value)->traceback;
22129         Py_XINCREF(tmp_tb);
22130         #else
22131         tmp_tb = PyException_GetTraceback(tmp_value);
22132         #endif
22133     }
22134   #elif CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK
22135     _PyErr_StackItem *exc_info = tstate->exc_info;
22136     tmp_type = exc_info->exc_type;
22137     tmp_value = exc_info->exc_value;
22138     tmp_tb = exc_info->exc_traceback;
22139     exc_info->exc_type = *type;
22140     exc_info->exc_value = *value;
22141     exc_info->exc_traceback = *tb;
22142   #else
22143     tmp_type = tstate->exc_type;
22144     tmp_value = tstate->exc_value;
22145     tmp_tb = tstate->exc_traceback;
22146     tstate->exc_type = *type;
22147     tstate->exc_value = *value;
22148     tstate->exc_traceback = *tb;
22149   #endif
22150     *type = tmp_type;
22151     *value = tmp_value;
22152     *tb = tmp_tb;
22153 }
22154 #else
22155 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_ExceptionSwap(PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb) {
22156     PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
22157     PyErr_GetExcInfo(&tmp_type, &tmp_value, &tmp_tb);
22158     PyErr_SetExcInfo(*type, *value, *tb);
22159     *type = tmp_type;
22160     *value = tmp_value;
22161     *tb = tmp_tb;

22165 /* RaiseArgTupleInvalid */
22166 static void __Pyx_RaiseArgtupleInvalid(
22167     const char* func_name,
22168     int exact,
22169     Py_ssize_t num_min,
22170     Py_ssize_t num_max,
22171     Py_ssize_t num_found)
22172 {
22173     Py_ssize_t num_expected;
22174     const char *more_or_less;
22175     if (num_found < num_min) {
22176         num_expected = num_min;
22177         more_or_less = "at least";
22178     } else {
22179         num_expected = num_max;
22180         more_or_less = "at most";
22181     }
22182     if (exact) {
22183         more_or_less = "exactly";
22184     }
22185     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22186                  "%.200s() takes %.8s %" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d positional argument%.1s (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
22187                  func_name, more_or_less, num_expected,
22188                  (num_expected == 1) ? "" : "s", num_found);
22189 }

22191 /* KeywordStringCheck */
22192 static int __Pyx_CheckKeywordStrings(
22193     PyObject *kw,
22194     const char* function_name,
22195     int kw_allowed)
22196 {
22197     PyObject* key = 0;
22198     Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
22199 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22200     if (!kw_allowed && PyDict_Next(kw, &pos, &key, 0))
22201         goto invalid_keyword;
22202     return 1;
22203 #else
22204     if (CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL && likely(PyTuple_Check(kw))) {
22205         Py_ssize_t kwsize;
22206 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
22207         kwsize = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(kw);
22208 #else
22209         kwsize = PyTuple_Size(kw);
22210         if (kwsize < 0) return 0;
22211 #endif
22212         if (unlikely(kwsize == 0))
22213             return 1;
22214         if (!kw_allowed) {
22215 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
22216             key = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kw, 0);
22217 #else
22218             key = PyTuple_GetItem(kw, pos);
22219             if (!key) return 0;
22220 #endif
22221             goto invalid_keyword;
22222         }
22223 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03090000
22224         for (pos = 0; pos < kwsize; pos++) {
22225 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
22226             key = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kw, pos);
22227 #else
22228             key = PyTuple_GetItem(kw, pos);
22229             if (!key) return 0;
22230 #endif
22231             if (unlikely(!PyUnicode_Check(key)))
22232                 goto invalid_keyword_type;
22233         }
22234 #endif
22235         return 1;
22236     }
22237     while (PyDict_Next(kw, &pos, &key, 0)) {
22238         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22239         if (unlikely(!PyString_Check(key)))
22240         #endif
22241             if (unlikely(!PyUnicode_Check(key)))
22242                 goto invalid_keyword_type;
22243     }
22244     if (!kw_allowed && unlikely(key))
22245         goto invalid_keyword;
22246     return 1;
22247 invalid_keyword_type:
22248     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22249         "%.200s() keywords must be strings", function_name);
22250     return 0;
22251 #endif
22252 invalid_keyword:
22253     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22254     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22255         "%.200s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%.200s'",
22256         function_name, PyString_AsString(key));
22257     #else
22258     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22259         "%s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%U'",
22260         function_name, key);
22261     #endif
22262     return 0;
22263 }
22264 
22265 /* RaiseDoubleKeywords */
22266 static void __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(
22267     const char* func_name,
22268     PyObject* kw_name)
22269 {
22270     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22271         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22272         "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%U'", func_name, kw_name);
22273         #else
22274         "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%s'", func_name,
22275         PyString_AsString(kw_name));
22276         #endif
22277 }
22278 
22279 /* ParseKeywords */
22280 static int __Pyx_ParseOptionalKeywords(
22281     PyObject *kwds,
22282     PyObject *const *kwvalues,
22283     PyObject **argnames[],
22284     PyObject *kwds2,
22285     PyObject *values[],
22286     Py_ssize_t num_pos_args,
22287     const char* function_name)
22288 {
22289     PyObject *key = 0, *value = 0;
22290     Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
22291     PyObject*** name;
22292     PyObject*** first_kw_arg = argnames + num_pos_args;
22293     int kwds_is_tuple = CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL && likely(PyTuple_Check(kwds));
22294     while (1) {
22295         Py_XDECREF(key); key = NULL;
22296         Py_XDECREF(value); value = NULL;
22297         if (kwds_is_tuple) {
22298             Py_ssize_t size;
22299 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
22300             size = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(kwds);
22301 #else
22302             size = PyTuple_Size(kwds);
22303             if (size < 0) goto bad;
22304 #endif
22305             if (pos >= size) break;
22306 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22307             key = __Pyx_PySequence_ITEM(kwds, pos);
22308             if (!key) goto bad;
22309 #elif CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
22310             key = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kwds, pos);
22311 #else
22312             key = PyTuple_GetItem(kwds, pos);
22313             if (!key) goto bad;
22314 #endif
22315             value = kwvalues[pos];
22316             pos++;
22317         }
22318         else
22319         {
22320             if (!PyDict_Next(kwds, &pos, &key, &value)) break;
22321 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22322             Py_INCREF(key);
22323 #endif
22324         }
22325         name = first_kw_arg;
22326         while (*name && (**name != key)) name++;
22327         if (*name) {
22328             values[name-argnames] = value;
22329 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22330             Py_INCREF(value);
22331             Py_DECREF(key);
22332 #endif
22333             key = NULL;
22334             value = NULL;
22335             continue;
22336         }
22337 #if !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22338         Py_INCREF(key);
22339 #endif
22340         Py_INCREF(value);
22341         name = first_kw_arg;
22342         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22343         if (likely(PyString_Check(key))) {
22344             while (*name) {
22345                 if ((CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**name) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
22346                         && _PyString_Eq(**name, key)) {
22347                     values[name-argnames] = value;
22348 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22349                     value = NULL;
22350 #endif
22351                     break;
22352                 }
22353                 name++;
22354             }
22355             if (*name) continue;
22356             else {
22357                 PyObject*** argname = argnames;
22358                 while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
22359                     if ((**argname == key) || (
22360                             (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**argname) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
22361                              && _PyString_Eq(**argname, key))) {
22362                         goto arg_passed_twice;
22363                     }
22364                     argname++;
22365                 }
22366             }
22367         } else
22368         #endif
22369         if (likely(PyUnicode_Check(key))) {
22370             while (*name) {
22371                 int cmp = (
22372                 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22373                     (__Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(**name) != __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(key)) ? 1 :
22374                 #endif
22375                     PyUnicode_Compare(**name, key)
22376                 );
22377                 if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
22378                 if (cmp == 0) {
22379                     values[name-argnames] = value;
22380 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22381                     value = NULL;
22382 #endif
22383                     break;
22384                 }
22385                 name++;
22386             }
22387             if (*name) continue;
22388             else {
22389                 PyObject*** argname = argnames;
22390                 while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
22391                     int cmp = (**argname == key) ? 0 :
22392                     #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22393                         (__Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(**argname) != __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(key)) ? 1 :
22394                     #endif
22395                         PyUnicode_Compare(**argname, key);
22396                     if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
22397                     if (cmp == 0) goto arg_passed_twice;
22398                     argname++;
22399                 }
22400             }
22401         } else
22402             goto invalid_keyword_type;
22403         if (kwds2) {
22404             if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItem(kwds2, key, value))) goto bad;
22405         } else {
22406             goto invalid_keyword;
22407         }
22408     }
22409     Py_XDECREF(key);
22410     Py_XDECREF(value);
22411     return 0;
22412 arg_passed_twice:
22413     __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(function_name, key);
22414     goto bad;
22415 invalid_keyword_type:
22416     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22417         "%.200s() keywords must be strings", function_name);
22418     goto bad;
22419 invalid_keyword:
22420     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22421     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22422         "%.200s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%.200s'",
22423         function_name, PyString_AsString(key));
22424     #else
22425     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22426         "%s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%U'",
22427         function_name, key);
22428     #endif
22429 bad:
22430     Py_XDECREF(key);
22431     Py_XDECREF(value);
22432     return -1;
22433 }
22434 
22435 /* RaiseUnexpectedTypeError */
22436 static int
22437 __Pyx_RaiseUnexpectedTypeError(const char *expected, PyObject *obj)
22438 {
22439     __Pyx_TypeName obj_type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(Py_TYPE(obj));
22440     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Expected %s, got " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME,
22441                  expected, obj_type_name);
22442     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(obj_type_name);
22443     return 0;
22444 }

22446 /* ArgTypeTest */
22447 static int __Pyx__ArgTypeTest(PyObject *obj, PyTypeObject *type, const char *name, int exact)
22448 {
22449     __Pyx_TypeName type_name;
22450     __Pyx_TypeName obj_type_name;
22451     if (unlikely(!type)) {
22452         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "Missing type object");
22453         return 0;
22454     }
22455     else if (exact) {
22456         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION == 2
22457         if ((type == &PyBaseString_Type) && likely(__Pyx_PyBaseString_CheckExact(obj))) return 1;
22458         #endif
22459     }
22460     else {
22461         if (likely(__Pyx_TypeCheck(obj, type))) return 1;
22462     }
22463     type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(type);
22464     obj_type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(Py_TYPE(obj));
22465     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22466         "Argument '%.200s' has incorrect type (expected " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME
22467         ", got " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME ")", name, type_name, obj_type_name);
22468     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(type_name);
22469     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(obj_type_name);
22470     return 0;
22471 }

22473 /* DictGetItem */
22474 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22475 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyDict_GetItem(PyObject *d, PyObject* key) {
22476     PyObject *value;
22477     value = PyDict_GetItemWithError(d, key);
22478     if (unlikely(!value)) {
22479         if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
22480             if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(key))) {
22481                 PyObject* args = PyTuple_Pack(1, key);
22482                 if (likely(args)) {
22483                     PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, args);
22484                     Py_DECREF(args);
22485                 }
22486             } else {
22487                 PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, key);
22488             }
22489         }
22490         return NULL;
22491     }
22492     Py_INCREF(value);
22493     return value;
22494 }

22497 /* GetItemInt */
22498 static PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(PyObject *o, PyObject* j) {
22499     PyObject *r;
22500     if (unlikely(!j)) return NULL;
22501     r = PyObject_GetItem(o, j);
22502     Py_DECREF(j);
22503     return r;
22504 }
22505 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_List_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
22506                                                               CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
22507                                                               CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
22508 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22509     Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
22510     if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
22511         wrapped_i += PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
22512     }
22513     if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyList_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
22514         PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
22515         Py_INCREF(r);
22516         return r;
22517     }
22518     return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
22519 #else
22520     return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
22521 #endif
22522 }
22523 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Tuple_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
22524                                                               CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
22525                                                               CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
22526 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
22527     Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
22528     if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
22529         wrapped_i += PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
22530     }
22531     if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
22532         PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
22533         Py_INCREF(r);
22534         return r;
22535     }
22536     return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
22537 #else
22538     return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
22539 #endif
22540 }
22541 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i, int is_list,
22542                                                      CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
22543                                                      CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
22544 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS && CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
22545     if (is_list || PyList_CheckExact(o)) {
22546         Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
22547         if ((!boundscheck) || (likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyList_GET_SIZE(o))))) {
22548             PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, n);
22549             Py_INCREF(r);
22550             return r;
22551         }
22552     }
22553     else if (PyTuple_CheckExact(o)) {
22554         Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
22555         if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
22556             PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, n);
22557             Py_INCREF(r);
22558             return r;
22559         }
22560     } else {
22561         PyMappingMethods *mm = Py_TYPE(o)->tp_as_mapping;
22562         PySequenceMethods *sm = Py_TYPE(o)->tp_as_sequence;
22563         if (mm && mm->mp_subscript) {
22564             PyObject *r, *key = PyInt_FromSsize_t(i);
22565             if (unlikely(!key)) return NULL;
22566             r = mm->mp_subscript(o, key);
22567             Py_DECREF(key);
22568             return r;
22569         }
22570         if (likely(sm && sm->sq_item)) {
22571             if (wraparound && unlikely(i < 0) && likely(sm->sq_length)) {
22572                 Py_ssize_t l = sm->sq_length(o);
22573                 if (likely(l >= 0)) {
22574                     i += l;
22575                 } else {
22576                     if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
22577                         return NULL;
22578                     PyErr_Clear();
22579                 }
22580             }
22581             return sm->sq_item(o, i);
22582         }
22583     }
22584 #else
22585     if (is_list || !PyMapping_Check(o)) {
22586         return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
22587     }
22588 #endif
22589     return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
22590 }

22600     PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
22601                  "need more than %" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d value%.1s to unpack",
22602                  index, (index == 1) ? "" : "s");

22605 /* IterFinish */
22606 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IterFinish(void) {
22607     PyObject* exc_type;
22608     __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
22609     __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
22610     exc_type = __Pyx_PyErr_CurrentExceptionType();
22611     if (unlikely(exc_type)) {
22612         if (unlikely(!__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyExc_StopIteration)))
22613             return -1;
22614         __Pyx_PyErr_Clear();
22615         return 0;
22616     }
22617     return 0;
22618 }

22620 /* UnpackItemEndCheck */
22621 static int __Pyx_IternextUnpackEndCheck(PyObject *retval, Py_ssize_t expected) {
22622     if (unlikely(retval)) {
22623         Py_DECREF(retval);
22624         __Pyx_RaiseTooManyValuesError(expected);
22625         return -1;
22626     }
22627     return __Pyx_IterFinish();
22628 }

22630 /* PyObjectCallOneArg */
22631 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallOneArg(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
22632     PyObject *args[2] = {NULL, arg};
22633     return __Pyx_PyObject_FastCall(func, args+1, 1 | __Pyx_PY_VECTORCALL_ARGUMENTS_OFFSET);
22634 }

22636 /* PyObjectGetMethod */
22637 static int __Pyx_PyObject_GetMethod(PyObject *obj, PyObject *name, PyObject **method) {
22638     PyObject *attr;
22639 #if CYTHON_UNPACK_METHODS && CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
22640     __Pyx_TypeName type_name;
22641     PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(obj);
22642     PyObject *descr;
22643     descrgetfunc f = NULL;
22644     PyObject **dictptr, *dict;
22645     int meth_found = 0;
22646     assert (*method == NULL);
22647     if (unlikely(tp->tp_getattro != PyObject_GenericGetAttr)) {
22648         attr = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(obj, name);
22649         goto try_unpack;
22650     }
22651     if (unlikely(tp->tp_dict == NULL) && unlikely(PyType_Ready(tp) < 0)) {
22652         return 0;
22653     }
22654     descr = _PyType_Lookup(tp, name);
22655     if (likely(descr != NULL)) {
22656         Py_INCREF(descr);
22657 #if defined(Py_TPFLAGS_METHOD_DESCRIPTOR) && Py_TPFLAGS_METHOD_DESCRIPTOR
22658         if (__Pyx_PyType_HasFeature(Py_TYPE(descr), Py_TPFLAGS_METHOD_DESCRIPTOR))
22659 #elif PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22660         #ifdef __Pyx_CyFunction_USED
22661         if (likely(PyFunction_Check(descr) || __Pyx_IS_TYPE(descr, &PyMethodDescr_Type) || __Pyx_CyFunction_Check(descr)))
22662         #else
22663         if (likely(PyFunction_Check(descr) || __Pyx_IS_TYPE(descr, &PyMethodDescr_Type)))
22664         #endif
22665 #else
22666         #ifdef __Pyx_CyFunction_USED
22667         if (likely(PyFunction_Check(descr) || __Pyx_CyFunction_Check(descr)))
22668         #else
22669         if (likely(PyFunction_Check(descr)))
22670         #endif
22671 #endif
22672         {
22673             meth_found = 1;
22674         } else {
22675             f = Py_TYPE(descr)->tp_descr_get;
22676             if (f != NULL && PyDescr_IsData(descr)) {
22677                 attr = f(descr, obj, (PyObject *)Py_TYPE(obj));
22678                 Py_DECREF(descr);
22679                 goto try_unpack;
22680             }
22681         }
22682     }
22683     dictptr = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(obj);
22684     if (dictptr != NULL && (dict = *dictptr) != NULL) {
22685         Py_INCREF(dict);
22686         attr = __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(dict, name);
22687         if (attr != NULL) {
22688             Py_INCREF(attr);
22689             Py_DECREF(dict);
22690             Py_XDECREF(descr);
22691             goto try_unpack;
22692         }
22693         Py_DECREF(dict);
22694     }
22695     if (meth_found) {
22696         *method = descr;
22697         return 1;
22698     }
22699     if (f != NULL) {
22700         attr = f(descr, obj, (PyObject *)Py_TYPE(obj));
22701         Py_DECREF(descr);
22702         goto try_unpack;
22703     }
22704     if (likely(descr != NULL)) {
22705         *method = descr;
22706         return 0;
22707     }
22708     type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(tp);
22709     PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
22710 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22711                  "'" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' object has no attribute '%U'",
22712                  type_name, name);
22713 #else
22714                  "'" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' object has no attribute '%.400s'",
22715                  type_name, PyString_AS_STRING(name));
22716 #endif
22717     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(type_name);
22718     return 0;
22719 #else
22720     attr = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(obj, name);
22721     goto try_unpack;
22722 #endif
22723 try_unpack:
22724 #if CYTHON_UNPACK_METHODS
22725     if (likely(attr) && PyMethod_Check(attr) && likely(PyMethod_GET_SELF(attr) == obj)) {
22726         PyObject *function = PyMethod_GET_FUNCTION(attr);
22727         Py_INCREF(function);
22728         Py_DECREF(attr);
22729         *method = function;
22730         return 1;
22731     }
22732 #endif
22733     *method = attr;
22734     return 0;
22735 }
22736 
22737 /* PyObjectCallMethod0 */
22738 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0(PyObject* obj, PyObject* method_name) {
22739     PyObject *method = NULL, *result = NULL;
22740     int is_method = __Pyx_PyObject_GetMethod(obj, method_name, &method);
22741     if (likely(is_method)) {
22742         result = __Pyx_PyObject_CallOneArg(method, obj);
22743         Py_DECREF(method);
22744         return result;
22745     }
22746     if (unlikely(!method)) goto bad;
22747     result = __Pyx_PyObject_CallNoArg(method);
22748     Py_DECREF(method);
22749 bad:
22750     return result;
22751 }

22754 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_RaiseNoneNotIterableError(void) {
22755     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "'NoneType' object is not iterable");
22756 }

22758 /* UnpackTupleError */
22759 static void __Pyx_UnpackTupleError(PyObject *t, Py_ssize_t index) {
22760     if (t == Py_None) {
22761       __Pyx_RaiseNoneNotIterableError();
22762     } else if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(t) < index) {
22763       __Pyx_RaiseNeedMoreValuesError(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(t));
22764     } else {
22765       __Pyx_RaiseTooManyValuesError(index);
22766     }
22767 }

22769 /* UnpackTuple2 */
22770 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_unpack_tuple2_exact(
22771         PyObject* tuple, PyObject** pvalue1, PyObject** pvalue2, int decref_tuple) {
22772     PyObject *value1 = NULL, *value2 = NULL;
22773 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22774     value1 = PySequence_ITEM(tuple, 0);  if (unlikely(!value1)) goto bad;
22775     value2 = PySequence_ITEM(tuple, 1);  if (unlikely(!value2)) goto bad;
22776 #else
22777     value1 = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, 0);  Py_INCREF(value1);
22778     value2 = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, 1);  Py_INCREF(value2);
22779 #endif
22780     if (decref_tuple) {
22781         Py_DECREF(tuple);
22782     }
22783     *pvalue1 = value1;
22784     *pvalue2 = value2;
22785     return 0;
22786 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22787 bad:
22788     Py_XDECREF(value1);
22789     Py_XDECREF(value2);
22790     if (decref_tuple) { Py_XDECREF(tuple); }
22791     return -1;
22792 #endif
22793 }
22794 static int __Pyx_unpack_tuple2_generic(PyObject* tuple, PyObject** pvalue1, PyObject** pvalue2,
22795                                        int has_known_size, int decref_tuple) {
22796     Py_ssize_t index;
22797     PyObject *value1 = NULL, *value2 = NULL, *iter = NULL;
22798     iternextfunc iternext;
22799     iter = PyObject_GetIter(tuple);
22800     if (unlikely(!iter)) goto bad;
22801     if (decref_tuple) { Py_DECREF(tuple); tuple = NULL; }
22802     iternext = __Pyx_PyObject_GetIterNextFunc(iter);
22803     value1 = iternext(iter); if (unlikely(!value1)) { index = 0; goto unpacking_failed; }
22804     value2 = iternext(iter); if (unlikely(!value2)) { index = 1; goto unpacking_failed; }
22805     if (!has_known_size && unlikely(__Pyx_IternextUnpackEndCheck(iternext(iter), 2))) goto bad;
22806     Py_DECREF(iter);
22807     *pvalue1 = value1;
22808     *pvalue2 = value2;
22809     return 0;
22810 unpacking_failed:
22811     if (!has_known_size && __Pyx_IterFinish() == 0)
22812         __Pyx_RaiseNeedMoreValuesError(index);
22813 bad:
22814     Py_XDECREF(iter);
22815     Py_XDECREF(value1);
22816     Py_XDECREF(value2);
22817     if (decref_tuple) { Py_XDECREF(tuple); }
22818     return -1;
22819 }
22820 
22821 /* dict_iter */
22822 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22823 #include <string.h>
22824 #endif
22825 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_dict_iterator(PyObject* iterable, int is_dict, PyObject* method_name,
22826                                                    Py_ssize_t* p_orig_length, int* p_source_is_dict) {
22827     is_dict = is_dict || likely(PyDict_CheckExact(iterable));
22828     *p_source_is_dict = is_dict;
22829     if (is_dict) {
22830 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22831         *p_orig_length = PyDict_Size(iterable);
22832         Py_INCREF(iterable);
22833         return iterable;
22834 #elif PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22835         static PyObject *py_items = NULL, *py_keys = NULL, *py_values = NULL;
22836         PyObject **pp = NULL;
22837         if (method_name) {
22838             const char *name = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(method_name);
22839             if (strcmp(name, "iteritems") == 0) pp = &py_items;
22840             else if (strcmp(name, "iterkeys") == 0) pp = &py_keys;
22841             else if (strcmp(name, "itervalues") == 0) pp = &py_values;
22842             if (pp) {
22843                 if (!*pp) {
22844                     *pp = PyUnicode_FromString(name + 4);
22845                     if (!*pp)
22846                         return NULL;
22847                 }
22848                 method_name = *pp;
22849             }
22850         }
22851 #endif
22852     }
22853     *p_orig_length = 0;
22854     if (method_name) {
22855         PyObject* iter;
22856         iterable = __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0(iterable, method_name);
22857         if (!iterable)
22858             return NULL;
22859 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22860         if (PyTuple_CheckExact(iterable) || PyList_CheckExact(iterable))
22861             return iterable;
22862 #endif
22863         iter = PyObject_GetIter(iterable);
22864         Py_DECREF(iterable);
22865         return iter;
22866     }
22867     return PyObject_GetIter(iterable);
22868 }
22869 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_dict_iter_next(
22870         PyObject* iter_obj, CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED Py_ssize_t orig_length, CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED Py_ssize_t* ppos,
22871         PyObject** pkey, PyObject** pvalue, PyObject** pitem, int source_is_dict) {
22872     PyObject* next_item;
22873 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
22874     if (source_is_dict) {
22875         PyObject *key, *value;
22876         if (unlikely(orig_length != PyDict_Size(iter_obj))) {
22877             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "dictionary changed size during iteration");
22878             return -1;
22879         }
22880         if (unlikely(!PyDict_Next(iter_obj, ppos, &key, &value))) {
22881             return 0;
22882         }
22883         if (pitem) {
22884             PyObject* tuple = PyTuple_New(2);
22885             if (unlikely(!tuple)) {
22886                 return -1;
22887             }
22888             Py_INCREF(key);
22889             Py_INCREF(value);
22890             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(tuple, 0, key);
22891             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(tuple, 1, value);
22892             *pitem = tuple;
22893         } else {
22894             if (pkey) {
22895                 Py_INCREF(key);
22896                 *pkey = key;
22897             }
22898             if (pvalue) {
22899                 Py_INCREF(value);
22900                 *pvalue = value;
22901             }
22902         }
22903         return 1;
22904     } else if (PyTuple_CheckExact(iter_obj)) {
22905         Py_ssize_t pos = *ppos;
22906         if (unlikely(pos >= PyTuple_GET_SIZE(iter_obj))) return 0;
22907         *ppos = pos + 1;
22908         next_item = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(iter_obj, pos);
22909         Py_INCREF(next_item);
22910     } else if (PyList_CheckExact(iter_obj)) {
22911         Py_ssize_t pos = *ppos;
22912         if (unlikely(pos >= PyList_GET_SIZE(iter_obj))) return 0;
22913         *ppos = pos + 1;
22914         next_item = PyList_GET_ITEM(iter_obj, pos);
22915         Py_INCREF(next_item);
22916     } else
22917 #endif
22918     {
22919         next_item = PyIter_Next(iter_obj);
22920         if (unlikely(!next_item)) {
22921             return __Pyx_IterFinish();
22922         }
22923     }
22924     if (pitem) {
22925         *pitem = next_item;
22926     } else if (pkey && pvalue) {
22927         if (__Pyx_unpack_tuple2(next_item, pkey, pvalue, source_is_dict, source_is_dict, 1))
22928             return -1;
22929     } else if (pkey) {
22930         *pkey = next_item;
22931     } else {
22932         *pvalue = next_item;
22933     }
22934     return 1;
22935 }
