22937 /* Import */
22938 static PyObject *__Pyx_Import(PyObject *name, PyObject *from_list, int level) {
22939     PyObject *module = 0;
22940     PyObject *empty_dict = 0;
22941     PyObject *empty_list = 0;
22942     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22943     PyObject *py_import;
22944     py_import = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_b, __pyx_n_s_import);
22945     if (unlikely(!py_import))
22946         goto bad;
22947     if (!from_list) {
22948         empty_list = PyList_New(0);
22949         if (unlikely(!empty_list))
22950             goto bad;
22951         from_list = empty_list;
22952     }
22953     #endif
22954     empty_dict = PyDict_New();
22955     if (unlikely(!empty_dict))
22956         goto bad;
22957     {
22958         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22959         if (level == -1) {
22960             if (strchr(__Pyx_MODULE_NAME, '.') != NULL) {
22961                 module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
22962                     name, __pyx_d, empty_dict, from_list, 1);
22963                 if (unlikely(!module)) {
22964                     if (unlikely(!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError)))
22965                         goto bad;
22966                     PyErr_Clear();
22967                 }
22968             }
22969             level = 0;
22970         }
22971         #endif
22972         if (!module) {
22973             #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22974             PyObject *py_level = PyInt_FromLong(level);
22975             if (unlikely(!py_level))
22976                 goto bad;
22977             module = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(py_import,
22978                 name, __pyx_d, empty_dict, from_list, py_level, (PyObject *)NULL);
22979             Py_DECREF(py_level);
22980             #else
22981             module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
22982                 name, __pyx_d, empty_dict, from_list, level);
22983             #endif
22984         }
22985     }
22986 bad:
22987     Py_XDECREF(empty_dict);
22988     Py_XDECREF(empty_list);
22989     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22990     Py_XDECREF(py_import);
22991     #endif
22992     return module;
22993 }

22995 /* ImportFrom */
22996 static PyObject* __Pyx_ImportFrom(PyObject* module, PyObject* name) {
22997     PyObject* value = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(module, name);
22998     if (unlikely(!value) && PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)) {
22999         const char* module_name_str = 0;
23000         PyObject* module_name = 0;
23001         PyObject* module_dot = 0;
23002         PyObject* full_name = 0;
23003         PyErr_Clear();
23004         module_name_str = PyModule_GetName(module);
23005         if (unlikely(!module_name_str)) { goto modbad; }
23006         module_name = PyUnicode_FromString(module_name_str);
23007         if (unlikely(!module_name)) { goto modbad; }
23008         module_dot = PyUnicode_Concat(module_name, __pyx_kp_u__3);
23009         if (unlikely(!module_dot)) { goto modbad; }
23010         full_name = PyUnicode_Concat(module_dot, name);
23011         if (unlikely(!full_name)) { goto modbad; }
23012         #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030700A1 || (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PYPY_VERSION_NUM  < 0x07030400)
23013         {
23014             PyObject *modules = PyImport_GetModuleDict();
23015             if (unlikely(!modules))
23016                 goto modbad;
23017             value = PyObject_GetItem(modules, full_name);
23018         }
23019         #else
23020         value = PyImport_GetModule(full_name);
23021         #endif
23022       modbad:
23023         Py_XDECREF(full_name);
23024         Py_XDECREF(module_dot);
23025         Py_XDECREF(module_name);
23026     }
23027     if (unlikely(!value)) {
23028         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ImportError,
23029         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23030             "cannot import name %.230s", PyString_AS_STRING(name));
23031         #else
23032             "cannot import name %S", name);
23033         #endif
23034     }
23035     return value;
23036 }

23051 /* HasAttr */
23052 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_HasAttr(PyObject *o, PyObject *n) {
23053     PyObject *r;
23054     if (unlikely(!__Pyx_PyBaseString_Check(n))) {
23055         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23056                         "hasattr(): attribute name must be string");
23057         return -1;
23058     }

23062         return 0;

23069 /* FixUpExtensionType */
23070 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS
23071 static int __Pyx_fix_up_extension_type_from_spec(PyType_Spec *spec, PyTypeObject *type) {
23072 #if PY_VERSION_HEX > 0x030900B1 || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23073     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(spec);
23074     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(type);
23075 #else
23076     const PyType_Slot *slot = spec->slots;
23077     while (slot && slot->slot && slot->slot != Py_tp_members)
23078         slot++;
23079     if (slot && slot->slot == Py_tp_members) {
23080         int changed = 0;
23081 #if !(PY_VERSION_HEX <= 0x030900b1 && CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON)
23082         const
23083 #endif
23084             PyMemberDef *memb = (PyMemberDef*) slot->pfunc;
23085         while (memb && memb->name) {
23086             if (memb->name[0] == '_' && memb->name[1] == '_') {
23087 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030900b1
23088                 if (strcmp(memb->name, "__weaklistoffset__") == 0) {
23089                     assert(memb->type == T_PYSSIZET);
23090                     assert(memb->flags == READONLY);
23091                     type->tp_weaklistoffset = memb->offset;
23092                     changed = 1;
23093                 }
23094                 else if (strcmp(memb->name, "__dictoffset__") == 0) {
23095                     assert(memb->type == T_PYSSIZET);
23096                     assert(memb->flags == READONLY);
23097                     type->tp_dictoffset = memb->offset;
23098                     changed = 1;
23099                 }
23100 #if CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL
23101                 else if (strcmp(memb->name, "__vectorcalloffset__") == 0) {
23102                     assert(memb->type == T_PYSSIZET);
23103                     assert(memb->flags == READONLY);
23104 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030800b4
23105                     type->tp_vectorcall_offset = memb->offset;
23106 #else
23107                     type->tp_print = (printfunc) memb->offset;
23108 #endif
23109                     changed = 1;
23110                 }
23111 #endif
23112 #else
23113                 if ((0));
23114 #endif
23115 #if PY_VERSION_HEX <= 0x030900b1 && CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
23116                 else if (strcmp(memb->name, "__module__") == 0) {
23117                     PyObject *descr;
23118                     assert(memb->type == T_OBJECT);
23119                     assert(memb->flags == 0 || memb->flags == READONLY);
23120                     descr = PyDescr_NewMember(type, memb);
23121                     if (unlikely(!descr))
23122                         return -1;
23123                     if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItem(type->tp_dict, PyDescr_NAME(descr), descr) < 0)) {
23124                         Py_DECREF(descr);
23125                         return -1;
23126                     }
23127                     Py_DECREF(descr);
23128                     changed = 1;
23129                 }
23130 #endif
23131             }
23132             memb++;
23133         }
23134         if (changed)
23135             PyType_Modified(type);
23136     }
23137 #endif
23138     return 0;
23139 }
23140 #endif

23142 /* ValidateBasesTuple */
23143 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API || CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS
23144 static int __Pyx_validate_bases_tuple(const char *type_name, Py_ssize_t dictoffset, PyObject *bases) {
23145     Py_ssize_t i, n;
23146 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
23147     n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(bases);
23148 #else
23149     n = PyTuple_Size(bases);
23150     if (n < 0) return -1;
23151 #endif
23152     for (i = 1; i < n; i++)
23153     {
23154 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23155         PyObject *b0 = PySequence_GetItem(bases, i);
23156         if (!b0) return -1;
23157 #elif CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
23158         PyObject *b0 = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(bases, i);
23159 #else
23160         PyObject *b0 = PyTuple_GetItem(bases, i);
23161         if (!b0) return -1;
23162 #endif
23163         PyTypeObject *b;
23164 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23165         if (PyClass_Check(b0))
23166         {
23167             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "base class '%.200s' is an old-style class",
23168                          PyString_AS_STRING(((PyClassObject*)b0)->cl_name));
23169 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23170             Py_DECREF(b0);
23171 #endif
23172             return -1;
23173         }
23174 #endif
23175         b = (PyTypeObject*) b0;
23176         if (!__Pyx_PyType_HasFeature(b, Py_TPFLAGS_HEAPTYPE))
23177         {
23178             __Pyx_TypeName b_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(b);
23179             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23180                 "base class '" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' is not a heap type", b_name);
23181             __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(b_name);
23182 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23183             Py_DECREF(b0);
23184 #endif
23185             return -1;
23186         }
23187         if (dictoffset == 0)
23188         {
23189             Py_ssize_t b_dictoffset = 0;
23190 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23191             b_dictoffset = b->tp_dictoffset;
23192 #else
23193             PyObject *py_b_dictoffset = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject*)b, "__dictoffset__");
23194             if (!py_b_dictoffset) goto dictoffset_return;
23195             b_dictoffset = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_b_dictoffset);
23196             Py_DECREF(py_b_dictoffset);
23197             if (b_dictoffset == -1 && PyErr_Occurred()) goto dictoffset_return;
23198 #endif
23199             if (b_dictoffset) {
23200                 {
23201                     __Pyx_TypeName b_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(b);
23202                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23203                         "extension type '%.200s' has no __dict__ slot, "
23204                         "but base type '" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' has: "
23205                         "either add 'cdef dict __dict__' to the extension type "
23206                         "or add '__slots__ = [...]' to the base type",
23207                         type_name, b_name);
23208                     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(b_name);
23209                 }
23210 #if !(CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY)
23211               dictoffset_return:
23212 #endif
23213 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23214                 Py_DECREF(b0);
23215 #endif
23216                 return -1;
23217             }
23218         }
23219 #if CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23220         Py_DECREF(b0);
23221 #endif
23222     }
23223     return 0;
23224 }
23225 #endif

23227 /* PyType_Ready */
23228 static int __Pyx_PyType_Ready(PyTypeObject *t) {
23229 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS || !(CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API) || defined(PYSTON_MAJOR_VERSION)
23230     (void)__Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0;
23231 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS
23232     (void)__Pyx_validate_bases_tuple;
23233 #endif
23234     return PyType_Ready(t);
23235 #else
23236     int r;
23237     PyObject *bases = __Pyx_PyType_GetSlot(t, tp_bases, PyObject*);
23238     if (bases && unlikely(__Pyx_validate_bases_tuple(t->tp_name, t->tp_dictoffset, bases) == -1))
23239         return -1;
23240 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x03050000 && !defined(PYSTON_MAJOR_VERSION)
23241     {
23242         int gc_was_enabled;
23243     #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030A00b1
23244         gc_was_enabled = PyGC_Disable();
23245         (void)__Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0;
23246     #else
23247         PyObject *ret, *py_status;
23248         PyObject *gc = NULL;
23249         #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030700a1 && (!CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PYPY_VERSION_NUM+0 >= 0x07030400)
23250         gc = PyImport_GetModule(__pyx_kp_u_gc);
23251         #endif
23252         if (unlikely(!gc)) gc = PyImport_Import(__pyx_kp_u_gc);
23253         if (unlikely(!gc)) return -1;
23254         py_status = __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0(gc, __pyx_kp_u_isenabled);
23255         if (unlikely(!py_status)) {
23256             Py_DECREF(gc);
23257             return -1;
23258         }
23259         gc_was_enabled = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(py_status);
23260         Py_DECREF(py_status);
23261         if (gc_was_enabled > 0) {
23262             ret = __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0(gc, __pyx_kp_u_disable);
23263             if (unlikely(!ret)) {
23264                 Py_DECREF(gc);
23265                 return -1;
23266             }
23267             Py_DECREF(ret);
23268         } else if (unlikely(gc_was_enabled == -1)) {
23269             Py_DECREF(gc);
23270             return -1;
23271         }
23272     #endif
23273         t->tp_flags |= Py_TPFLAGS_HEAPTYPE;
23274 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030A0000
23275         t->tp_flags |= Py_TPFLAGS_IMMUTABLETYPE;
23276 #endif
23277 #else
23278         (void)__Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0;
23279 #endif
23280     r = PyType_Ready(t);
23281 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x03050000 && !defined(PYSTON_MAJOR_VERSION)
23282         t->tp_flags &= ~Py_TPFLAGS_HEAPTYPE;
23283     #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030A00b1
23284         if (gc_was_enabled)
23285             PyGC_Enable();
23286     #else
23287         if (gc_was_enabled) {
23288             PyObject *tp, *v, *tb;
23289             PyErr_Fetch(&tp, &v, &tb);
23290             ret = __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethod0(gc, __pyx_kp_u_enable);
23291             if (likely(ret || r == -1)) {
23292                 Py_XDECREF(ret);
23293                 PyErr_Restore(tp, v, tb);
23294             } else {
23295                 Py_XDECREF(tp);
23296                 Py_XDECREF(v);
23297                 Py_XDECREF(tb);
23298                 r = -1;
23299             }
23300         }
23301         Py_DECREF(gc);
23302     #endif
23303     }
23304 #endif
23305     return r;
23306 #endif
23307 }

23309 /* PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict */
23310 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS && CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03070000
23311 static PyObject *__Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(PyTypeObject *tp, PyObject *attr_name) {
23312     __Pyx_TypeName type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(tp);
23313     PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
23314 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23315                  "'" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' object has no attribute '%U'",
23316                  type_name, attr_name);
23317 #else
23318                  "'" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' object has no attribute '%.400s'",
23319                  type_name, PyString_AS_STRING(attr_name));
23320 #endif
23321     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(type_name);
23322     return NULL;
23323 }
23324 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict(PyObject* obj, PyObject* attr_name) {
23325     PyObject *descr;
23326     PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(obj);
23327     if (unlikely(!PyString_Check(attr_name))) {
23328         return PyObject_GenericGetAttr(obj, attr_name);
23329     }
23330     assert(!tp->tp_dictoffset);
23331     descr = _PyType_Lookup(tp, attr_name);
23332     if (unlikely(!descr)) {
23333         return __Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(tp, attr_name);
23334     }
23335     Py_INCREF(descr);
23336     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23337     if (likely(PyType_HasFeature(Py_TYPE(descr), Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS)))
23338     #endif
23339     {
23340         descrgetfunc f = Py_TYPE(descr)->tp_descr_get;
23341         if (unlikely(f)) {
23342             PyObject *res = f(descr, obj, (PyObject *)tp);
23343             Py_DECREF(descr);
23344             return res;
23345         }
23346     }
23347     return descr;
23348 }
23349 #endif

23352 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS && CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03070000
23353 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_GenericGetAttr(PyObject* obj, PyObject* attr_name) {
23354     if (unlikely(Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_dictoffset)) {
23355         return PyObject_GenericGetAttr(obj, attr_name);
23356     }
23357     return __Pyx_PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict(obj, attr_name);

23364     if (unlikely(!ob))
23365         goto bad;
23366 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23367     if (unlikely(PyObject_SetAttr((PyObject *) type, __pyx_n_s_pyx_vtable, ob) < 0))
23368 #else
23369     if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItem(type->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_pyx_vtable, ob) < 0))
23370 #endif

23374 bad:

23379 /* GetVTable */
23380 static void* __Pyx_GetVtable(PyTypeObject *type) {
23381     void* ptr;
23382 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23383     PyObject *ob = PyObject_GetAttr((PyObject *)type, __pyx_n_s_pyx_vtable);
23384 #else
23385     PyObject *ob = PyObject_GetItem(type->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_pyx_vtable);
23386 #endif
23387     if (!ob)
23388         goto bad;
23389     ptr = PyCapsule_GetPointer(ob, 0);
23390     if (!ptr && !PyErr_Occurred())
23391         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "invalid vtable found for imported type");
23392     Py_DECREF(ob);
23393     return ptr;
23394 bad:
23395     Py_XDECREF(ob);
23396     return NULL;
23397 }

23399 /* MergeVTables */
23400 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23401 static int __Pyx_MergeVtables(PyTypeObject *type) {
23402     int i;
23403     void** base_vtables;
23404     __Pyx_TypeName tp_base_name;
23405     __Pyx_TypeName base_name;
23406     void* unknown = (void*)-1;
23407     PyObject* bases = type->tp_bases;
23408     int base_depth = 0;
23409     {
23410         PyTypeObject* base = type->tp_base;
23411         while (base) {
23412             base_depth += 1;
23413             base = base->tp_base;
23414         }
23415     }
23416     base_vtables = (void**) malloc(sizeof(void*) * (size_t)(base_depth + 1));
23417     base_vtables[0] = unknown;
23418     for (i = 1; i < PyTuple_GET_SIZE(bases); i++) {
23419         void* base_vtable = __Pyx_GetVtable(((PyTypeObject*)PyTuple_GET_ITEM(bases, i)));
23420         if (base_vtable != NULL) {
23421             int j;
23422             PyTypeObject* base = type->tp_base;
23423             for (j = 0; j < base_depth; j++) {
23424                 if (base_vtables[j] == unknown) {
23425                     base_vtables[j] = __Pyx_GetVtable(base);
23426                     base_vtables[j + 1] = unknown;
23427                 }
23428                 if (base_vtables[j] == base_vtable) {
23429                     break;
23430                 } else if (base_vtables[j] == NULL) {
23431                     goto bad;
23432                 }
23433                 base = base->tp_base;
23434             }
23435         }
23436     }
23437     PyErr_Clear();
23438     free(base_vtables);
23439     return 0;
23440 bad:
23441     tp_base_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(type->tp_base);
23442     base_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName((PyTypeObject*)PyTuple_GET_ITEM(bases, i));
23443     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23444         "multiple bases have vtable conflict: '" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "' and '" __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME "'", tp_base_name, base_name);
23445     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(tp_base_name);
23446     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(base_name);
23447     free(base_vtables);
23448     return -1;
23449 }

23452 /* SetupReduce */
23453 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23454 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(PyObject* meth, PyObject* name) {
23455   int ret;
23456   PyObject *name_attr;
23457   name_attr = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(meth, __pyx_n_s_name);
23458   if (likely(name_attr)) {
23459       ret = PyObject_RichCompareBool(name_attr, name, Py_EQ);
23460   } else {
23461       ret = -1;
23462   }
23463   if (unlikely(ret < 0)) {
23464       PyErr_Clear();
23465       ret = 0;
23466   }
23467   Py_XDECREF(name_attr);

23470 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce(PyObject* type_obj) {
23471     int ret = 0;
23472     PyObject *object_reduce = NULL;
23473     PyObject *object_getstate = NULL;
23474     PyObject *object_reduce_ex = NULL;
23475     PyObject *reduce = NULL;
23476     PyObject *reduce_ex = NULL;
23477     PyObject *reduce_cython = NULL;
23478     PyObject *setstate = NULL;
23479     PyObject *setstate_cython = NULL;
23480     PyObject *getstate = NULL;
23481 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
23482     getstate = _PyType_Lookup((PyTypeObject*)type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate);
23483 #else
23484     getstate = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate);
23485     if (!getstate && PyErr_Occurred()) {
23486         goto __PYX_BAD;
23487     }
23488 #endif
23489     if (getstate) {
23490 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
23491         object_getstate = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_getstate);
23492 #else
23493         object_getstate = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_getstate);
23494         if (!object_getstate && PyErr_Occurred()) {
23495             goto __PYX_BAD;
23496         }
23497 #endif
23498         if (object_getstate != getstate) {
23499             goto __PYX_GOOD;
23500         }
23501     }
23502 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
23503     object_reduce_ex = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto __PYX_BAD;
23504 #else
23505     object_reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto __PYX_BAD;
23506 #endif
23507     reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (unlikely(!reduce_ex)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23508     if (reduce_ex == object_reduce_ex) {
23509 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
23510         object_reduce = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto __PYX_BAD;
23511 #else
23512         object_reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto __PYX_BAD;
23513 #endif
23514         reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (unlikely(!reduce)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23515         if (reduce == object_reduce || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(reduce, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython)) {
23516             reduce_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython);
23517             if (likely(reduce_cython)) {
23518                 ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce, reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23519                 ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23520             } else if (reduce == object_reduce || PyErr_Occurred()) {
23521                 goto __PYX_BAD;
23522             }
23523             setstate = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate);
23524             if (!setstate) PyErr_Clear();
23525             if (!setstate || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(setstate, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython)) {
23526                 setstate_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython);
23527                 if (likely(setstate_cython)) {
23528                     ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate, setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23529                     ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto __PYX_BAD;
23530                 } else if (!setstate || PyErr_Occurred()) {
23531                     goto __PYX_BAD;
23532                 }
23533             }
23534             PyType_Modified((PyTypeObject*)type_obj);
23535         }
23536     }
23537     goto __PYX_GOOD;
23538 __PYX_BAD:
23539     if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
23540         __Pyx_TypeName type_obj_name =
23541             __Pyx_PyType_GetName((PyTypeObject*)type_obj);
23542         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
23543             "Unable to initialize pickling for " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME, type_obj_name);
23544         __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(type_obj_name);
23545     }
23546     ret = -1;
23547 __PYX_GOOD:
23548 #if !CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
23549     Py_XDECREF(object_reduce);
23550     Py_XDECREF(object_reduce_ex);
23551     Py_XDECREF(object_getstate);
23552     Py_XDECREF(getstate);
23553 #endif
23554     Py_XDECREF(reduce);
23555     Py_XDECREF(reduce_ex);
23556     Py_XDECREF(reduce_cython);
23557     Py_XDECREF(setstate);
23558     Py_XDECREF(setstate_cython);
23559     return ret;
23560 }

23563 /* TypeImport */
23564 #ifndef __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType_3_0_11
23565 #define __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType_3_0_11
23566 static PyTypeObject *__Pyx_ImportType_3_0_11(PyObject *module, const char *module_name, const char *class_name,
23567     size_t size, size_t alignment, enum __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_3_0_11 check_size)
23568 {
23569     PyObject *result = 0;
23570     char warning[200];
23571     Py_ssize_t basicsize;
23572     Py_ssize_t itemsize;
23573 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23574     PyObject *py_basicsize;
23575     PyObject *py_itemsize;
23576 #endif
23577     result = PyObject_GetAttrString(module, class_name);
23578     if (!result)
23579         goto bad;
23580     if (!PyType_Check(result)) {
23581         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23582             "%.200s.%.200s is not a type object",
23583             module_name, class_name);
23584         goto bad;
23585     }
23586 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23587     basicsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_basicsize;
23588     itemsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_itemsize;
23589 #else
23590     py_basicsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__basicsize__");
23591     if (!py_basicsize)
23592         goto bad;
23593     basicsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_basicsize);
23594     Py_DECREF(py_basicsize);
23595     py_basicsize = 0;
23596     if (basicsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
23597         goto bad;
23598     py_itemsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__itemsize__");
23599     if (!py_itemsize)
23600         goto bad;
23601     itemsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_itemsize);
23602     Py_DECREF(py_itemsize);
23603     py_itemsize = 0;
23604     if (itemsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
23605         goto bad;
23606 #endif
23607     if (itemsize) {
23608         if (size % alignment) {
23609             alignment = size % alignment;
23610         }
23611         if (itemsize < (Py_ssize_t)alignment)
23612             itemsize = (Py_ssize_t)alignment;
23613     }
23614     if ((size_t)(basicsize + itemsize) < size) {
23615         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
23616             "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
23617             "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
23618             module_name, class_name, size, basicsize+itemsize);
23619         goto bad;
23620     }
23621     if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Error_3_0_11 &&
23622             ((size_t)basicsize > size || (size_t)(basicsize + itemsize) < size)) {
23623         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
23624             "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
23625             "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd-%zd from PyObject",
23626             module_name, class_name, size, basicsize, basicsize+itemsize);
23627         goto bad;
23628     }
23629     else if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Warn_3_0_11 && (size_t)basicsize > size) {
23630         PyOS_snprintf(warning, sizeof(warning),
23631             "%s.%s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
23632             "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
23633             module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
23634         if (PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, warning, 0) < 0) goto bad;
23635     }
23636     return (PyTypeObject *)result;
23637 bad:
23638     Py_XDECREF(result);
23639     return NULL;
23640 }
23641 #endif

23643 /* ImportDottedModule */
23644 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23645 static PyObject *__Pyx__ImportDottedModule_Error(PyObject *name, PyObject *parts_tuple, Py_ssize_t count) {
23646     PyObject *partial_name = NULL, *slice = NULL, *sep = NULL;
23647     if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) {
23648         PyErr_Clear();
23649     }
23650     if (likely(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(parts_tuple) == count)) {
23651         partial_name = name;
23652     } else {
23653         slice = PySequence_GetSlice(parts_tuple, 0, count);
23654         if (unlikely(!slice))
23655             goto bad;
23656         sep = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(".", 1);
23657         if (unlikely(!sep))
23658             goto bad;
23659         partial_name = PyUnicode_Join(sep, slice);
23660     }
23661     PyErr_Format(
23662 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23663         PyExc_ImportError,
23664         "No module named '%s'", PyString_AS_STRING(partial_name));
23665 #else
23666 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030600B1
23667         PyExc_ModuleNotFoundError,
23668 #else
23669         PyExc_ImportError,
23670 #endif
23671         "No module named '%U'", partial_name);
23672 #endif
23673 bad:
23674     Py_XDECREF(sep);
23675     Py_XDECREF(slice);
23676     Py_XDECREF(partial_name);
23677     return NULL;
23678 }
23679 #endif
23680 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23681 static PyObject *__Pyx__ImportDottedModule_Lookup(PyObject *name) {
23682     PyObject *imported_module;
23683 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030700A1 || (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PYPY_VERSION_NUM  < 0x07030400)
23684     PyObject *modules = PyImport_GetModuleDict();
23685     if (unlikely(!modules))
23686         return NULL;
23687     imported_module = __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(modules, name);
23688     Py_XINCREF(imported_module);
23689 #else
23690     imported_module = PyImport_GetModule(name);
23691 #endif
23692     return imported_module;
23693 }
23694 #endif
23695 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23696 static PyObject *__Pyx_ImportDottedModule_WalkParts(PyObject *module, PyObject *name, PyObject *parts_tuple) {
23697     Py_ssize_t i, nparts;
23698     nparts = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(parts_tuple);
23699     for (i=1; i < nparts && module; i++) {
23700         PyObject *part, *submodule;
23701 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23702         part = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(parts_tuple, i);
23703 #else
23704         part = PySequence_ITEM(parts_tuple, i);
23705 #endif
23706         submodule = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(module, part);
23707 #if !(CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS)
23708         Py_DECREF(part);
23709 #endif
23710         Py_DECREF(module);
23711         module = submodule;
23712     }
23713     if (unlikely(!module)) {
23714         return __Pyx__ImportDottedModule_Error(name, parts_tuple, i);
23715     }
23716     return module;
23717 }
23718 #endif
23719 static PyObject *__Pyx__ImportDottedModule(PyObject *name, PyObject *parts_tuple) {
23720 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23721     PyObject *module, *from_list, *star = __pyx_n_s__10;
23722     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(parts_tuple);
23723     from_list = PyList_New(1);
23724     if (unlikely(!from_list))
23725         return NULL;
23726     Py_INCREF(star);
23727     PyList_SET_ITEM(from_list, 0, star);
23728     module = __Pyx_Import(name, from_list, 0);
23729     Py_DECREF(from_list);
23730     return module;
23731 #else
23732     PyObject *imported_module;
23733     PyObject *module = __Pyx_Import(name, NULL, 0);
23734     if (!parts_tuple || unlikely(!module))
23735         return module;
23736     imported_module = __Pyx__ImportDottedModule_Lookup(name);
23737     if (likely(imported_module)) {
23738         Py_DECREF(module);
23739         return imported_module;
23740     }
23741     PyErr_Clear();
23742     return __Pyx_ImportDottedModule_WalkParts(module, name, parts_tuple);
23743 #endif
23744 }
23745 static PyObject *__Pyx_ImportDottedModule(PyObject *name, PyObject *parts_tuple) {
23746 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030400B1
23747     PyObject *module = __Pyx__ImportDottedModule_Lookup(name);
23748     if (likely(module)) {
23749         PyObject *spec = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(module, __pyx_n_s_spec);
23750         if (likely(spec)) {

23752             if (likely(!unsafe || !__Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(unsafe))) {
23753                 Py_DECREF(spec);
23754                 spec = NULL;
23755             }
23756             Py_XDECREF(unsafe);
23757         }
23758         if (likely(!spec)) {
23759             PyErr_Clear();
23760             return module;
23761         }
23762         Py_DECREF(spec);
23763         Py_DECREF(module);
23764     } else if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
23765         PyErr_Clear();
23766     }
23767 #endif
23768     return __Pyx__ImportDottedModule(name, parts_tuple);

23776 /* FetchCommonType */
23777 static int __Pyx_VerifyCachedType(PyObject *cached_type,
23778                                const char *name,
23779                                Py_ssize_t basicsize,
23780                                Py_ssize_t expected_basicsize) {
23781     if (!PyType_Check(cached_type)) {
23782         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23783             "Shared Cython type %.200s is not a type object", name);
23784         return -1;
23785     }
23786     if (basicsize != expected_basicsize) {
23787         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23788             "Shared Cython type %.200s has the wrong size, try recompiling",
23789             name);
23790         return -1;
23791     }
23792     return 0;
23793 }
23794 #if !CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS
23795 static PyTypeObject* __Pyx_FetchCommonType(PyTypeObject* type) {
23796     PyObject* abi_module;
23797     const char* object_name;
23798     PyTypeObject *cached_type = NULL;
23799     abi_module = __Pyx_FetchSharedCythonABIModule();
23800     if (!abi_module) return NULL;
23801     object_name = strrchr(type->tp_name, '.');
23802     object_name = object_name ? object_name+1 : type->tp_name;
23803     cached_type = (PyTypeObject*) PyObject_GetAttrString(abi_module, object_name);
23804     if (cached_type) {
23805         if (__Pyx_VerifyCachedType(
23806               (PyObject *)cached_type,
23807               object_name,
23808               cached_type->tp_basicsize,
23809               type->tp_basicsize) < 0) {
23810             goto bad;
23811         }
23812         goto done;
23813     }
23814     if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)) goto bad;
23815     PyErr_Clear();
23816     if (PyType_Ready(type) < 0) goto bad;
23817     if (PyObject_SetAttrString(abi_module, object_name, (PyObject *)type) < 0)
23818         goto bad;
23819     Py_INCREF(type);
23820     cached_type = type;
23821 done:
23822     Py_DECREF(abi_module);
23823     return cached_type;
23824 bad:
23825     Py_XDECREF(cached_type);
23826     cached_type = NULL;
23827     goto done;
23828 }
23829 #else
23830 static PyTypeObject *__Pyx_FetchCommonTypeFromSpec(PyObject *module, PyType_Spec *spec, PyObject *bases) {
23831     PyObject *abi_module, *cached_type = NULL;
23832     const char* object_name = strrchr(spec->name, '.');
23833     object_name = object_name ? object_name+1 : spec->name;
23834     abi_module = __Pyx_FetchSharedCythonABIModule();
23835     if (!abi_module) return NULL;
23836     cached_type = PyObject_GetAttrString(abi_module, object_name);
23837     if (cached_type) {
23838         Py_ssize_t basicsize;
23839 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
23840         PyObject *py_basicsize;
23841         py_basicsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(cached_type, "__basicsize__");
23842         if (unlikely(!py_basicsize)) goto bad;

23844         Py_DECREF(py_basicsize);

23847 #else

23849 #endif
23850         if (__Pyx_VerifyCachedType(
23851               cached_type,
23852               object_name,
23853               basicsize,
23854               spec->basicsize) < 0) {
23855             goto bad;
23856         }
23857         goto done;
23858     }
23859     if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)) goto bad;
23860     PyErr_Clear();
23861     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(module);
23862     cached_type = __Pyx_PyType_FromModuleAndSpec(abi_module, spec, bases);
23863     if (unlikely(!cached_type)) goto bad;
23864     if (unlikely(__Pyx_fix_up_extension_type_from_spec(spec, (PyTypeObject *) cached_type) < 0)) goto bad;
23865     if (PyObject_SetAttrString(abi_module, object_name, cached_type) < 0) goto bad;

23877 /* PyVectorcallFastCallDict */
23878 #if CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL
23879 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyVectorcall_FastCallDict_kw(PyObject *func, __pyx_vectorcallfunc vc, PyObject *const *args, size_t nargs, PyObject *kw)
23880 {
23881     PyObject *res = NULL;
23882     PyObject *kwnames;
23883     PyObject **newargs;
23884     PyObject **kwvalues;
23885     Py_ssize_t i, pos;
23886     size_t j;
23887     PyObject *key, *value;
23888     unsigned long keys_are_strings;
23889     Py_ssize_t nkw = PyDict_GET_SIZE(kw);
23890     newargs = (PyObject **)PyMem_Malloc((nargs + (size_t)nkw) * sizeof(args[0]));
23891     if (unlikely(newargs == NULL)) {
23892         PyErr_NoMemory();
23893         return NULL;
23894     }
23895     for (j = 0; j < nargs; j++) newargs[j] = args[j];
23896     kwnames = PyTuple_New(nkw);
23897     if (unlikely(kwnames == NULL)) {
23898         PyMem_Free(newargs);
23899         return NULL;
23900     }
23901     kwvalues = newargs + nargs;
23902     pos = i = 0;
23903     keys_are_strings = Py_TPFLAGS_UNICODE_SUBCLASS;
23904     while (PyDict_Next(kw, &pos, &key, &value)) {
23905         keys_are_strings &= Py_TYPE(key)->tp_flags;
23906         Py_INCREF(key);
23907         Py_INCREF(value);
23908         PyTuple_SET_ITEM(kwnames, i, key);
23909         kwvalues[i] = value;
23910         i++;
23911     }
23912     if (unlikely(!keys_are_strings)) {
23913         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "keywords must be strings");
23914         goto cleanup;
23915     }
23916     res = vc(func, newargs, nargs, kwnames);
23917 cleanup:
23918     Py_DECREF(kwnames);
23919     for (i = 0; i < nkw; i++)
23920         Py_DECREF(kwvalues[i]);
23921     PyMem_Free(newargs);
23922     return res;
23923 }
23924 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_PyVectorcall_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, __pyx_vectorcallfunc vc, PyObject *const *args, size_t nargs, PyObject *kw)
23925 {
23926     if (likely(kw == NULL) || PyDict_GET_SIZE(kw) == 0) {
23927         return vc(func, args, nargs, NULL);
23928     }
23929     return __Pyx_PyVectorcall_FastCallDict_kw(func, vc, args, nargs, kw);
23930 }
23931 #endif

24110 static int
24111 __Pyx_CyFunction_init_defaults(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *op) {
24112     int result = 0;
24113     PyObject *res = op->defaults_getter((PyObject *) op);
24114     if (unlikely(!res))
24115         return -1;
24116     #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
24117     op->defaults_tuple = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(res, 0);
24118     Py_INCREF(op->defaults_tuple);
24119     op->defaults_kwdict = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(res, 1);
24120     Py_INCREF(op->defaults_kwdict);
24121     #else
24122     op->defaults_tuple = __Pyx_PySequence_ITEM(res, 0);
24123     if (unlikely(!op->defaults_tuple)) result = -1;
24124     else {
24125         op->defaults_kwdict = __Pyx_PySequence_ITEM(res, 1);
24126         if (unlikely(!op->defaults_kwdict)) result = -1;
24127     }
24128     #endif
24129     Py_DECREF(res);
24130     return result;
24131 }

24134     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(context);

24136         value = Py_None;
24137     } else if (unlikely(value != Py_None && !PyTuple_Check(value))) {
24138         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
24139                         "__defaults__ must be set to a tuple object");

24146     return 0;

24220 static PyObject *
24221 __Pyx_CyFunction_get_is_coroutine(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *op, void *context) {
24222     int is_coroutine;
24223     CYTHON_UNUSED_VAR(context);
24224     if (op->func_is_coroutine) {
24225         return __Pyx_NewRef(op->func_is_coroutine);
24226     }
24227     is_coroutine = op->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_COROUTINE;
24228 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x03050000
24229     if (is_coroutine) {
24230         PyObject *module, *fromlist, *marker = __pyx_n_s_is_coroutine;
24231         fromlist = PyList_New(1);
24232         if (unlikely(!fromlist)) return NULL;
24233         Py_INCREF(marker);
24234 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
24235         PyList_SET_ITEM(fromlist, 0, marker);
24236 #else
24237         if (unlikely(PyList_SetItem(fromlist, 0, marker) < 0)) {
24238             Py_DECREF(marker);
24239             Py_DECREF(fromlist);
24240             return NULL;
24241         }
24242 #endif
24243         module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(__pyx_n_s_asyncio_coroutines, NULL, NULL, fromlist, 0);
24244         Py_DECREF(fromlist);
24245         if (unlikely(!module)) goto ignore;
24246         op->func_is_coroutine = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(module, marker);
24247         Py_DECREF(module);
24248         if (likely(op->func_is_coroutine)) {
24249             return __Pyx_NewRef(op->func_is_coroutine);
24250         }
24251 ignore:
24252         PyErr_Clear();
24253     }
24254 #endif
24255     op->func_is_coroutine = __Pyx_PyBool_FromLong(is_coroutine);
24256     return __Pyx_NewRef(op->func_is_coroutine);
24257 }

24337 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_Init(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *op, PyMethodDef *ml, int flags, PyObject* qualname,
24338                                        PyObject *closure, PyObject *module, PyObject* globals, PyObject* code) {
24339 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24340     PyCFunctionObject *cf = (PyCFunctionObject*) op;
24341 #endif
24342     if (unlikely(op == NULL))
24343         return NULL;
24344 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24345     op->func = PyCFunction_NewEx(ml, (PyObject*)op, module);
24346     if (unlikely(!op->func)) return NULL;
24347 #endif
24348     op->flags = flags;
24349     __Pyx_CyFunction_weakreflist(op) = NULL;
24350 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24351     cf->m_ml = ml;
24352     cf->m_self = (PyObject *) op;
24353 #endif
24354     Py_XINCREF(closure);
24355     op->func_closure = closure;
24356 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24357     Py_XINCREF(module);
24358     cf->m_module = module;
24359 #endif
24360     op->func_dict = NULL;
24361     op->func_name = NULL;
24362     Py_INCREF(qualname);
24363     op->func_qualname = qualname;
24364     op->func_doc = NULL;
24365 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030900B1 || CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24366     op->func_classobj = NULL;
24367 #else
24368     ((PyCMethodObject*)op)->mm_class = NULL;
24369 #endif
24370     op->func_globals = globals;
24371     Py_INCREF(op->func_globals);
24372     Py_XINCREF(code);
24373     op->func_code = code;
24374     op->defaults_pyobjects = 0;
24375     op->defaults_size = 0;
24376     op->defaults = NULL;
24377     op->defaults_tuple = NULL;
24378     op->defaults_kwdict = NULL;
24379     op->defaults_getter = NULL;
24380     op->func_annotations = NULL;
24381     op->func_is_coroutine = NULL;
24382 #if CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL
24383     switch (ml->ml_flags & (METH_VARARGS | METH_FASTCALL | METH_NOARGS | METH_O | METH_KEYWORDS | METH_METHOD)) {
24384     case METH_NOARGS:
24385         __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(op) = __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_NOARGS;
24386         break;
24387     case METH_O:
24388         __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(op) = __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_O;
24389         break;
24390     case METH_METHOD | METH_FASTCALL | METH_KEYWORDS:
24391         __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(op) = __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_FASTCALL_KEYWORDS_METHOD;
24392         break;
24393     case METH_FASTCALL | METH_KEYWORDS:
24394         __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(op) = __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_FASTCALL_KEYWORDS;
24395         break;
24396     case METH_VARARGS | METH_KEYWORDS:
24397         __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(op) = NULL;
24398         break;
24399     default:
24400         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "Bad call flags for CyFunction");
24401         Py_DECREF(op);
24402         return NULL;
24403     }
24404 #endif
24405     return (PyObject *) op;
24406 }
24407 static int
24408 __Pyx_CyFunction_clear(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *m)
24409 {
24410     Py_CLEAR(m->func_closure);
24411 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24412     Py_CLEAR(m->func);
24413 #else
24414     Py_CLEAR(((PyCFunctionObject*)m)->m_module);
24415 #endif
24416     Py_CLEAR(m->func_dict);
24417     Py_CLEAR(m->func_name);
24418     Py_CLEAR(m->func_qualname);
24419     Py_CLEAR(m->func_doc);
24420     Py_CLEAR(m->func_globals);
24421     Py_CLEAR(m->func_code);
24422 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24423 #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030900B1
24424     Py_CLEAR(__Pyx_CyFunction_GetClassObj(m));
24425 #else
24426     {
24427         PyObject *cls = (PyObject*) ((PyCMethodObject *) (m))->mm_class;
24428         ((PyCMethodObject *) (m))->mm_class = NULL;
24429         Py_XDECREF(cls);
24430     }
24431 #endif
24432 #endif
24433     Py_CLEAR(m->defaults_tuple);
24434     Py_CLEAR(m->defaults_kwdict);
24435     Py_CLEAR(m->func_annotations);
24436     Py_CLEAR(m->func_is_coroutine);
24437     if (m->defaults) {
24438         PyObject **pydefaults = __Pyx_CyFunction_Defaults(PyObject *, m);
24439         int i;
24440         for (i = 0; i < m->defaults_pyobjects; i++)
24441             Py_XDECREF(pydefaults[i]);
24442         PyObject_Free(m->defaults);
24443         m->defaults = NULL;
24444     }
24445     return 0;
24446 }

24498 static PyObject * __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(PyObject *func, PyObject *self, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
24499 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24500     PyObject *f = ((__pyx_CyFunctionObject*)func)->func;
24501     PyObject *py_name = NULL;
24502     PyCFunction meth;
24503     int flags;
24504     meth = PyCFunction_GetFunction(f);
24505     if (unlikely(!meth)) return NULL;
24506     flags = PyCFunction_GetFlags(f);
24507     if (unlikely(flags < 0)) return NULL;
24508 #else
24509     PyCFunctionObject* f = (PyCFunctionObject*)func;
24510     PyCFunction meth = f->m_ml->ml_meth;
24511     int flags = f->m_ml->ml_flags;
24512 #endif
24513     Py_ssize_t size;
24514     switch (flags & (METH_VARARGS | METH_KEYWORDS | METH_NOARGS | METH_O)) {
24515     case METH_VARARGS:
24516         if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0))
24517             return (*meth)(self, arg);
24518         break;
24519     case METH_VARARGS | METH_KEYWORDS:
24520         return (*(PyCFunctionWithKeywords)(void*)meth)(self, arg, kw);
24521     case METH_NOARGS:
24522         if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0)) {
24523 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
24524             size = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(arg);
24525 #else
24526             size = PyTuple_Size(arg);
24527             if (unlikely(size < 0)) return NULL;
24528 #endif
24529             if (likely(size == 0))
24530                 return (*meth)(self, NULL);
24531 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24532             py_name = __Pyx_CyFunction_get_name((__pyx_CyFunctionObject*)func, NULL);
24533             if (!py_name) return NULL;
24534             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24535                 "%.200S() takes no arguments (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
24536                 py_name, size);
24537             Py_DECREF(py_name);
24538 #else
24539             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24540                 "%.200s() takes no arguments (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
24541                 f->m_ml->ml_name, size);
24542 #endif
24543             return NULL;
24544         }
24545         break;
24546     case METH_O:
24547         if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0)) {
24548 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
24549             size = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(arg);
24550 #else
24551             size = PyTuple_Size(arg);
24552             if (unlikely(size < 0)) return NULL;
24553 #endif
24554             if (likely(size == 1)) {
24555                 PyObject *result, *arg0;
24556                 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
24557                 arg0 = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(arg, 0);
24558                 #else
24559                 arg0 = __Pyx_PySequence_ITEM(arg, 0); if (unlikely(!arg0)) return NULL;
24560                 #endif
24561                 result = (*meth)(self, arg0);
24562                 #if !(CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS)
24563                 Py_DECREF(arg0);
24564                 #endif
24565                 return result;
24566             }
24567 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24568             py_name = __Pyx_CyFunction_get_name((__pyx_CyFunctionObject*)func, NULL);
24569             if (!py_name) return NULL;
24570             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24571                 "%.200S() takes exactly one argument (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
24572                 py_name, size);
24573             Py_DECREF(py_name);
24574 #else
24575             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24576                 "%.200s() takes exactly one argument (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
24577                 f->m_ml->ml_name, size);
24578 #endif
24579             return NULL;
24580         }
24581         break;
24582     default:
24583         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "Bad call flags for CyFunction");
24584         return NULL;
24585     }
24586 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24587     py_name = __Pyx_CyFunction_get_name((__pyx_CyFunctionObject*)func, NULL);
24588     if (!py_name) return NULL;
24589     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%.200S() takes no keyword arguments",
24590                  py_name);
24591     Py_DECREF(py_name);
24592 #else
24593     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%.200s() takes no keyword arguments",
24594                  f->m_ml->ml_name);
24595 #endif
24596     return NULL;
24597 }
24598 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_Call(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
24599     PyObject *self, *result;
24600 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24601     self = PyCFunction_GetSelf(((__pyx_CyFunctionObject*)func)->func);
24602     if (unlikely(!self) && PyErr_Occurred()) return NULL;
24603 #else
24604     self = ((PyCFunctionObject*)func)->m_self;
24605 #endif
24606     result = __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(func, self, arg, kw);
24607     return result;
24608 }
24609 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_CallAsMethod(PyObject *func, PyObject *args, PyObject *kw) {
24610     PyObject *result;
24611     __pyx_CyFunctionObject *cyfunc = (__pyx_CyFunctionObject *) func;
24612 #if CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL
24613      __pyx_vectorcallfunc vc = __Pyx_CyFunction_func_vectorcall(cyfunc);
24614     if (vc) {
24615 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
24616         return __Pyx_PyVectorcall_FastCallDict(func, vc, &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0), (size_t)PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args), kw);
24617 #else
24618         (void) &__Pyx_PyVectorcall_FastCallDict;
24619         return PyVectorcall_Call(func, args, kw);
24620 #endif
24621     }
24622 #endif
24623     if ((cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_CCLASS) && !(cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_STATICMETHOD)) {
24624         Py_ssize_t argc;
24625         PyObject *new_args;
24626         PyObject *self;
24627 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS
24628         argc = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args);
24629 #else
24630         argc = PyTuple_Size(args);
24631         if (unlikely(!argc) < 0) return NULL;
24632 #endif
24633         new_args = PyTuple_GetSlice(args, 1, argc);
24634         if (unlikely(!new_args))
24635             return NULL;
24636         self = PyTuple_GetItem(args, 0);
24637         if (unlikely(!self)) {
24638             Py_DECREF(new_args);
24639 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION > 2
24640             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24641                          "unbound method %.200S() needs an argument",
24642                          cyfunc->func_qualname);
24643 #else
24644             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
24645                             "unbound method needs an argument");
24646 #endif
24647             return NULL;
24648         }
24649         result = __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(func, self, new_args, kw);
24650         Py_DECREF(new_args);
24651     } else {
24652         result = __Pyx_CyFunction_Call(func, args, kw);
24653     }
24654     return result;
24655 }
24656 #if CYTHON_METH_FASTCALL
24657 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_CheckArgs(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *cyfunc, Py_ssize_t nargs, PyObject *kwnames)
24658 {
24659     int ret = 0;
24660     if ((cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_CCLASS) && !(cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_STATICMETHOD)) {
24661         if (unlikely(nargs < 1)) {
24662             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%.200s() needs an argument",
24663                          ((PyCFunctionObject*)cyfunc)->m_ml->ml_name);
24664             return -1;
24665         }
24666         ret = 1;
24667     }
24668     if (unlikely(kwnames) && unlikely(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(kwnames))) {
24669         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24670                      "%.200s() takes no keyword arguments", ((PyCFunctionObject*)cyfunc)->m_ml->ml_name);
24671         return -1;
24672     }
24673     return ret;
24674 }
24675 static PyObject * __Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_NOARGS(PyObject *func, PyObject *const *args, size_t nargsf, PyObject *kwnames)
24676 {
24677     __pyx_CyFunctionObject *cyfunc = (__pyx_CyFunctionObject *)func;
24678     PyMethodDef* def = ((PyCFunctionObject*)cyfunc)->m_ml;
24679 #if CYTHON_BACKPORT_VECTORCALL
24680     Py_ssize_t nargs = (Py_ssize_t)nargsf;
24681 #else
24682     Py_ssize_t nargs = PyVectorcall_NARGS(nargsf);
24683 #endif
24684     PyObject *self;
24685     switch (__Pyx_CyFunction_Vectorcall_CheckArgs(cyfunc, nargs, kwnames)) {
24686     case 1:
24687         self = args[0];
24688         args += 1;
24689         nargs -= 1;
24690         break;
24691     case 0:
24692         self = ((PyCFunctionObject*)cyfunc)->m_self;
24693         break;
24694     default:
24695         return NULL;
24696     }
24697     if (unlikely(nargs != 0)) {
24698         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24699             "%.200s() takes no arguments (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
24700             def->ml_name, nargs);
24701         return NULL;
24702     }
24703     return def->ml_meth(self, NULL);
24704 }

24939 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_New(PyMethodDef *ml, int flags, PyObject* qualname,
24940                                       PyObject *closure, PyObject *module, PyObject* globals, PyObject* code) {
24941     PyObject *op = __Pyx_CyFunction_Init(
24942         PyObject_GC_New(__pyx_CyFunctionObject, __pyx_CyFunctionType),
24943         ml, flags, qualname, closure, module, globals, code
24944     );
24945     if (likely(op)) {
24946         PyObject_GC_Track(op);
24947     }
24948     return op;
24949 }

24951 /* CLineInTraceback */
24952 #ifndef CYTHON_CLINE_IN_TRACEBACK
24953 static int __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(PyThreadState *tstate, int c_line) {
24954     PyObject *use_cline;
24955     PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
24956 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
24957     PyObject **cython_runtime_dict;
24958 #endif
24959     CYTHON_MAYBE_UNUSED_VAR(tstate);
24960     if (unlikely(!__pyx_cython_runtime)) {
24961         return c_line;
24962     }
24963     __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
24964 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
24965     cython_runtime_dict = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(__pyx_cython_runtime);
24966     if (likely(cython_runtime_dict)) {
24967         __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(
24968             use_cline, *cython_runtime_dict,
24969             __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(*cython_runtime_dict, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback))
24970     } else
24971 #endif
24972     {
24973       PyObject *use_cline_obj = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStrNoError(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback);
24974       if (use_cline_obj) {
24975         use_cline = PyObject_Not(use_cline_obj) ? Py_False : Py_True;
24976         Py_DECREF(use_cline_obj);
24977       } else {
24978         PyErr_Clear();
24979         use_cline = NULL;
24980       }
24981     }
24982     if (!use_cline) {
24983         c_line = 0;
24984         (void) PyObject_SetAttr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback, Py_False);
24985     }
24986     else if (use_cline == Py_False || (use_cline != Py_True && PyObject_Not(use_cline) != 0)) {
24987         c_line = 0;
24988     }
24989     __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
24990     return c_line;
24991 }
24992 #endif
24993 
24994 /* CodeObjectCache */
24995 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
24996 static int __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries, int count, int code_line) {
24997     int start = 0, mid = 0, end = count - 1;
24998     if (end >= 0 && code_line > entries[end].code_line) {
24999         return count;
25000     }
25001     while (start < end) {
25002         mid = start + (end - start) / 2;
25003         if (code_line < entries[mid].code_line) {
25004             end = mid;
25005         } else if (code_line > entries[mid].code_line) {
25006              start = mid + 1;
25007         } else {
25008             return mid;
25009         }
25010     }
25011     if (code_line <= entries[mid].code_line) {
25012         return mid;
25013     } else {
25014         return mid + 1;
25015     }
25016 }
25017 static PyCodeObject *__pyx_find_code_object(int code_line) {
25018     PyCodeObject* code_object;
25019     int pos;
25020     if (unlikely(!code_line) || unlikely(!__pyx_code_cache.entries)) {
25021         return NULL;
25022     }
25023     pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
25024     if (unlikely(pos >= __pyx_code_cache.count) || unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line != code_line)) {
25025         return NULL;
25026     }
25027     code_object = __pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_object;
25028     Py_INCREF(code_object);
25029     return code_object;
25030 }
25031 static void __pyx_insert_code_object(int code_line, PyCodeObject* code_object) {
25032     int pos, i;
25033     __Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries = __pyx_code_cache.entries;
25034     if (unlikely(!code_line)) {
25035         return;
25036     }
25037     if (unlikely(!entries)) {
25038         entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Malloc(64*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
25039         if (likely(entries)) {
25040             __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
25041             __pyx_code_cache.max_count = 64;
25042             __pyx_code_cache.count = 1;
25043             entries[0].code_line = code_line;
25044             entries[0].code_object = code_object;
25045             Py_INCREF(code_object);
25046         }
25047         return;
25048     }
25049     pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
25050     if ((pos < __pyx_code_cache.count) && unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line == code_line)) {
25051         PyCodeObject* tmp = entries[pos].code_object;
25052         entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
25053         Py_DECREF(tmp);
25054         return;
25055     }
25056     if (__pyx_code_cache.count == __pyx_code_cache.max_count) {
25057         int new_max = __pyx_code_cache.max_count + 64;
25058         entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Realloc(
25059             __pyx_code_cache.entries, ((size_t)new_max) * sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
25060         if (unlikely(!entries)) {
25061             return;
25062         }
25063         __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
25064         __pyx_code_cache.max_count = new_max;
25065     }
25066     for (i=__pyx_code_cache.count; i>pos; i--) {
25067         entries[i] = entries[i-1];
25068     }
25069     entries[pos].code_line = code_line;
25070     entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
25071     __pyx_code_cache.count++;
25072     Py_INCREF(code_object);
25073 }
25074 #endif

25076 /* AddTraceback */
25077 #include "compile.h"
25078 #include "frameobject.h"
25079 #include "traceback.h"
25080 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030b00a6 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
25081   #ifndef Py_BUILD_CORE
25082     #define Py_BUILD_CORE 1
25083   #endif
25084   #include "internal/pycore_frame.h"
25085 #endif
25086 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
25087 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyCode_Replace_For_AddTraceback(PyObject *code, PyObject *scratch_dict,
25088                                                        PyObject *firstlineno, PyObject *name) {
25089     PyObject *replace = NULL;
25090     if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItemString(scratch_dict, "co_firstlineno", firstlineno))) return NULL;
25091     if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItemString(scratch_dict, "co_name", name))) return NULL;
25092     replace = PyObject_GetAttrString(code, "replace");
25093     if (likely(replace)) {
25094         PyObject *result;
25095         result = PyObject_Call(replace, __pyx_empty_tuple, scratch_dict);
25096         Py_DECREF(replace);
25097         return result;
25098     }
25099     PyErr_Clear();
25100     #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX < 0x030780000
25101     {
25102         PyObject *compiled = NULL, *result = NULL;
25103         if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItemString(scratch_dict, "code", code))) return NULL;
25104         if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItemString(scratch_dict, "type", (PyObject*)(&PyType_Type)))) return NULL;
25105         compiled = Py_CompileString(
25106             "out = type(code)(\n"
25107             "  code.co_argcount, code.co_kwonlyargcount, code.co_nlocals, code.co_stacksize,\n"
25108             "  code.co_flags, code.co_code, code.co_consts, code.co_names,\n"
25109             "  code.co_varnames, code.co_filename, co_name, co_firstlineno,\n"
25110             "  code.co_lnotab)\n", "<dummy>", Py_file_input);
25111         if (!compiled) return NULL;
25112         result = PyEval_EvalCode(compiled, scratch_dict, scratch_dict);
25113         Py_DECREF(compiled);
25114         if (!result) PyErr_Print();
25115         Py_DECREF(result);
25116         result = PyDict_GetItemString(scratch_dict, "out");
25117         if (result) Py_INCREF(result);
25118         return result;
25119     }
25120     #else
25121     return NULL;
25122     #endif
25123 }
25124 static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const char *funcname, int c_line,
25125                                int py_line, const char *filename) {
25126     PyObject *code_object = NULL, *py_py_line = NULL, *py_funcname = NULL, *dict = NULL;
25127     PyObject *replace = NULL, *getframe = NULL, *frame = NULL;
25128     PyObject *exc_type, *exc_value, *exc_traceback;
25129     int success = 0;
25130     if (c_line) {
25131         (void) __pyx_cfilenm;
25132         (void) __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(__Pyx_PyThreadState_Current, c_line);
25133     }
25134     PyErr_Fetch(&exc_type, &exc_value, &exc_traceback);
25135     code_object = Py_CompileString("_getframe()", filename, Py_eval_input);
25136     if (unlikely(!code_object)) goto bad;
25137     py_py_line = PyLong_FromLong(py_line);
25138     if (unlikely(!py_py_line)) goto bad;
25139     py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromString(funcname);
25140     if (unlikely(!py_funcname)) goto bad;
25141     dict = PyDict_New();
25142     if (unlikely(!dict)) goto bad;
25143     {
25144         PyObject *old_code_object = code_object;
25145         code_object = __Pyx_PyCode_Replace_For_AddTraceback(code_object, dict, py_py_line, py_funcname);
25146         Py_DECREF(old_code_object);
25147     }
25148     if (unlikely(!code_object)) goto bad;
25149     getframe = PySys_GetObject("_getframe");
25150     if (unlikely(!getframe)) goto bad;
25151     if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItemString(dict, "_getframe", getframe))) goto bad;
25152     frame = PyEval_EvalCode(code_object, dict, dict);
25153     if (unlikely(!frame) || frame == Py_None) goto bad;
25154     success = 1;
25155   bad:
25156     PyErr_Restore(exc_type, exc_value, exc_traceback);
25157     Py_XDECREF(code_object);
25158     Py_XDECREF(py_py_line);
25159     Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
25160     Py_XDECREF(dict);
25161     Py_XDECREF(replace);
25162     if (success) {
25163         PyTraceBack_Here(
25164             (struct _frame*)frame);
25165     }
25166     Py_XDECREF(frame);
25167 }
25168 #else
25169 static PyCodeObject* __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
25170             const char *funcname, int c_line,
25171             int py_line, const char *filename) {
25172     PyCodeObject *py_code = NULL;
25173     PyObject *py_funcname = NULL;
25174     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25175     PyObject *py_srcfile = NULL;
25176     py_srcfile = PyString_FromString(filename);
25177     if (!py_srcfile) goto bad;
25178     #endif
25179     if (c_line) {
25180         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25181         py_funcname = PyString_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
25182         if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
25183         #else
25184         py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
25185         if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
25186         funcname = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(py_funcname);
25187         if (!funcname) goto bad;
25188         #endif
25189     }
25190     else {
25191         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25192         py_funcname = PyString_FromString(funcname);
25193         if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
25194         #endif
25195     }
25196     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25197     py_code = __Pyx_PyCode_New(
25198         0,
25199         0,
25200         0,
25201         0,
25202         0,
25203         0,
25204         __pyx_empty_bytes, /*PyObject *code,*/
25205         __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *consts,*/
25206         __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *names,*/
25207         __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *varnames,*/
25208         __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *freevars,*/
25209         __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *cellvars,*/
25210         py_srcfile,   /*PyObject *filename,*/
25211         py_funcname,  /*PyObject *name,*/
25212         py_line,
25213         __pyx_empty_bytes  /*PyObject *lnotab*/
25214     );
25215     Py_DECREF(py_srcfile);
25216     #else
25217     py_code = PyCode_NewEmpty(filename, funcname, py_line);
25218     #endif
25219     Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
25220     return py_code;
25221 bad:
25222     Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
25223     #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25224     Py_XDECREF(py_srcfile);
25225     #endif
25226     return NULL;
25227 }
25228 static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const char *funcname, int c_line,
25229                                int py_line, const char *filename) {
25230     PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
25231     PyFrameObject *py_frame = 0;
25232     PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
25233     PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
25234     if (c_line) {
25235         c_line = __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(tstate, c_line);
25236     }
25237     py_code = __pyx_find_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line);
25238     if (!py_code) {
25239         __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
25240         py_code = __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
25241             funcname, c_line, py_line, filename);
25242         if (!py_code) {
25243             /* If the code object creation fails, then we should clear the 
25244                fetched exception references and propagate the new exception */
25245             Py_XDECREF(ptype);
25246             Py_XDECREF(pvalue);
25247             Py_XDECREF(ptraceback);
25248             goto bad;
25249         }
25250         __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
25251         __pyx_insert_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line, py_code);
25252     }
25253     py_frame = PyFrame_New(
25254         tstate,            /*PyThreadState *tstate,*/
25255         py_code,           /*PyCodeObject *code,*/
25256         __pyx_d,    /*PyObject *globals,*/
25257         0                  /*PyObject *locals*/
25258     );
25259     if (!py_frame) goto bad;
25260     __Pyx_PyFrame_SetLineNumber(py_frame, py_line);
25261     PyTraceBack_Here(py_frame);
25262 bad:
25263     Py_XDECREF(py_code);
25264     Py_XDECREF(py_frame);
25265 }
25266 #endif

25268 /* CIntFromPyVerify */
25269 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
25270     __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 0)
25271 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
25272     __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 1)
25273 #define __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, exc)\
25274     {\
25275         func_type value = func_value;\
25276         if (sizeof(target_type) < sizeof(func_type)) {\
25277             if (unlikely(value != (func_type) (target_type) value)) {\
25278                 func_type zero = 0;\
25279                 if (exc && unlikely(value == (func_type)-1 && PyErr_Occurred()))\
25280                     return (target_type) -1;\
25281                 if (is_unsigned && unlikely(value < zero))\
25282                     goto raise_neg_overflow;\
25283                 else\
25284                     goto raise_overflow;\
25285             }\
25286         }\
25287         return (target_type) value;\
25288     }

25290 /* CIntToPy */
25291 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_From_int(int value) {
25292 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
25293 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
25294 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wconversion"
25295 #endif
25296     const int neg_one = (int) -1, const_zero = (int) 0;
25297 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
25298 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
25299 #endif
25300     const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25301     if (is_unsigned) {
25302         if (sizeof(int) < sizeof(long)) {
25303             return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25304         } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25305             return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
25306 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25307         } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25308             return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25309 #endif
25310         }
25311     } else {
25312         if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(long)) {
25313             return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25314 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25315         } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25316             return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25317 #endif
25318         }
25319     }
25320     {
25321         unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
25322 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030d00A4
25323         if (is_unsigned) {
25324             return PyLong_FromUnsignedNativeBytes(bytes, sizeof(value), -1);
25325         } else {
25326             return PyLong_FromNativeBytes(bytes, sizeof(value), -1);
25327         }
25328 #elif !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030d0000
25329         int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25330         return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(int),
25331                                      little, !is_unsigned);
25332 #else
25333         int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25334         PyObject *from_bytes, *result = NULL;
25335         PyObject *py_bytes = NULL, *arg_tuple = NULL, *kwds = NULL, *order_str = NULL;
25336         from_bytes = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject*)&PyLong_Type, "from_bytes");
25337         if (!from_bytes) return NULL;
25338         py_bytes = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize((char*)bytes, sizeof(int));
25339         if (!py_bytes) goto limited_bad;
25340         order_str = PyUnicode_FromString(little ? "little" : "big");
25341         if (!order_str) goto limited_bad;
25342         arg_tuple = PyTuple_Pack(2, py_bytes, order_str);
25343         if (!arg_tuple) goto limited_bad;
25344         if (!is_unsigned) {
25345             kwds = PyDict_New();
25346             if (!kwds) goto limited_bad;
25347             if (PyDict_SetItemString(kwds, "signed", __Pyx_NewRef(Py_True))) goto limited_bad;
25348         }
25349         result = PyObject_Call(from_bytes, arg_tuple, kwds);
25350         limited_bad:
25351         Py_XDECREF(kwds);
25352         Py_XDECREF(arg_tuple);
25353         Py_XDECREF(order_str);
25354         Py_XDECREF(py_bytes);
25355         Py_XDECREF(from_bytes);
25356         return result;
25357 #endif
25358     }
25359 }
25360 
25361 /* CIntFromPy */
25362 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyInt_As_int(PyObject *x) {
25363 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
25364 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
25365 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wconversion"
25366 #endif
25367     const int neg_one = (int) -1, const_zero = (int) 0;
25368 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
25369 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
25370 #endif
25371     const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25372 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25373     if (likely(PyInt_Check(x))) {
25374         if ((sizeof(int) < sizeof(long))) {
25375             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, long, PyInt_AS_LONG(x))
25376         } else {
25377             long val = PyInt_AS_LONG(x);
25378             if (is_unsigned && unlikely(val < 0)) {
25379                 goto raise_neg_overflow;
25380             }
25381             return (int) val;
25382         }
25383     }
25384 #endif
25385     if (unlikely(!PyLong_Check(x))) {
25386         int val;
25387         PyObject *tmp = __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(x);
25388         if (!tmp) return (int) -1;
25389         val = __Pyx_PyInt_As_int(tmp);
25390         Py_DECREF(tmp);
25391         return val;
25392     }
25393     if (is_unsigned) {
25394 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
25395         if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyLong_IsNeg(x))) {
25396             goto raise_neg_overflow;
25397         } else if (__Pyx_PyLong_IsCompact(x)) {
25398             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, __Pyx_compact_upylong, __Pyx_PyLong_CompactValueUnsigned(x))
25399         } else {
25400             const digit* digits = __Pyx_PyLong_Digits(x);
25401             assert(__Pyx_PyLong_DigitCount(x) > 1);
25402             switch (__Pyx_PyLong_DigitCount(x)) {
25403                 case 2:
25404                     if ((8 * sizeof(int) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25405                         if ((8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25406                             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25407                         } else if ((8 * sizeof(int) >= 2 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25408                             return (int) (((((int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
25409                         }
25410                     }
25411                     break;
25412                 case 3:
25413                     if ((8 * sizeof(int) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25414                         if ((8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25415                             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25416                         } else if ((8 * sizeof(int) >= 3 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25417                             return (int) (((((((int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
25418                         }
25419                     }
25420                     break;
25421                 case 4:
25422                     if ((8 * sizeof(int) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25423                         if ((8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25424                             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25425                         } else if ((8 * sizeof(int) >= 4 * PyLong_SHIFT)) {
25426                             return (int) (((((((((int)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
25427                         }
25428                     }
25429                     break;
25430             }
25431         }
25432 #endif
25433 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030C00A7
25434         if (unlikely(Py_SIZE(x) < 0)) {
25435             goto raise_neg_overflow;
25436         }
25437 #else
25438         {
25439             int result = PyObject_RichCompareBool(x, Py_False, Py_LT);
25440             if (unlikely(result < 0))
25441                 return (int) -1;
25442             if (unlikely(result == 1))
25443                 goto raise_neg_overflow;
25444         }
25445 #endif
25446         if ((sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned long))) {
25447             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(int, unsigned long, PyLong_AsUnsignedLong(x))
25448 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25449         } else if ((sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG))) {
25450             __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(int, unsigned PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsUnsignedLongLong(x))
25451 #endif
25452         }
25453     } else {
25454 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS

25907         if (sizeof(long) < sizeof(long)) {
25908             return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25909         } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25910             return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
25911 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25912         } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25913             return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25914 #endif
25915         }
25916     } else {
25917         if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(long)) {
25918             return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25919 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25920         } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25921             return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25922 #endif
25923         }
25924     }
25925     {
25926         unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
25927 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API && PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030d00A4
25928         if (is_unsigned) {
25929             return PyLong_FromUnsignedNativeBytes(bytes, sizeof(value), -1);
25930         } else {
25931             return PyLong_FromNativeBytes(bytes, sizeof(value), -1);
25932         }
25933 #elif !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030d0000
25934         int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25935         return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(long),
25936                                      little, !is_unsigned);
25937 #else
25938         int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25939         PyObject *from_bytes, *result = NULL;
25940         PyObject *py_bytes = NULL, *arg_tuple = NULL, *kwds = NULL, *order_str = NULL;
25941         from_bytes = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject*)&PyLong_Type, "from_bytes");
25942         if (!from_bytes) return NULL;
25943         py_bytes = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize((char*)bytes, sizeof(long));
25944         if (!py_bytes) goto limited_bad;
25945         order_str = PyUnicode_FromString(little ? "little" : "big");
25946         if (!order_str) goto limited_bad;
25947         arg_tuple = PyTuple_Pack(2, py_bytes, order_str);
25948         if (!arg_tuple) goto limited_bad;
25949         if (!is_unsigned) {
25950             kwds = PyDict_New();
25951             if (!kwds) goto limited_bad;
25952             if (PyDict_SetItemString(kwds, "signed", __Pyx_NewRef(Py_True))) goto limited_bad;
25953         }
25954         result = PyObject_Call(from_bytes, arg_tuple, kwds);
25955         limited_bad:
25956         Py_XDECREF(kwds);
25957         Py_XDECREF(arg_tuple);
25958         Py_XDECREF(order_str);
25959         Py_XDECREF(py_bytes);
25960         Py_XDECREF(from_bytes);
25961         return result;
25962 #endif
25963     }
25964 }
