25982 /* FastTypeChecks */
25983 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
25984 static int __Pyx_InBases(PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
25985     while (a) {
25986         a = __Pyx_PyType_GetSlot(a, tp_base, PyTypeObject*);
25987         if (a == b)
25988             return 1;
25989     }
25990     return b == &PyBaseObject_Type;
25991 }
25992 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IsSubtype(PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
25993     PyObject *mro;
25994     if (a == b) return 1;
25995     mro = a->tp_mro;
25996     if (likely(mro)) {
25997         Py_ssize_t i, n;
25998         n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(mro);
25999         for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
26000             if (PyTuple_GET_ITEM(mro, i) == (PyObject *)b)
26001                 return 1;
26002         }
26003         return 0;
26004     }
26005     return __Pyx_InBases(a, b);
26006 }
26007 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IsAnySubtype2(PyTypeObject *cls, PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
26008     PyObject *mro;
26009     if (cls == a || cls == b) return 1;
26010     mro = cls->tp_mro;
26011     if (likely(mro)) {
26012         Py_ssize_t i, n;
26013         n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(mro);
26014         for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
26015             PyObject *base = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(mro, i);
26016             if (base == (PyObject *)a || base == (PyObject *)b)
26017                 return 1;
26018         }
26019         return 0;
26020     }
26021     return __Pyx_InBases(cls, a) || __Pyx_InBases(cls, b);
26022 }
26023 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION == 2
26024 static int __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type1, PyObject* exc_type2) {
26025     PyObject *exception, *value, *tb;
26026     int res;
26027     __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
26028     __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
26029     __Pyx_ErrFetch(&exception, &value, &tb);
26030     res = exc_type1 ? PyObject_IsSubclass(err, exc_type1) : 0;
26031     if (unlikely(res == -1)) {
26032         PyErr_WriteUnraisable(err);
26033         res = 0;
26034     }
26035     if (!res) {
26036         res = PyObject_IsSubclass(err, exc_type2);
26037         if (unlikely(res == -1)) {
26038             PyErr_WriteUnraisable(err);
26039             res = 0;
26040         }
26041     }
26042     __Pyx_ErrRestore(exception, value, tb);
26043     return res;
26044 }
26045 #else
26046 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type1, PyObject *exc_type2) {
26047     if (exc_type1) {
26048         return __Pyx_IsAnySubtype2((PyTypeObject*)err, (PyTypeObject*)exc_type1, (PyTypeObject*)exc_type2);
26049     } else {
26050         return __Pyx_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject*)err, (PyTypeObject*)exc_type2);
26051     }
26052 }
26053 #endif
26054 static int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
26055     Py_ssize_t i, n;
26056     assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type));
26057     n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
26058 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
26059     for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
26060         if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
26061     }
26062 #endif
26063     for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
26064         PyObject *t = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i);
26065         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26066         if (likely(exc_type == t)) return 1;
26067         #endif
26068         if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(t))) {
26069             if (__Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(exc_type, NULL, t)) return 1;
26070         } else {
26071         }
26072     }
26073     return 0;
26074 }
26075 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type) {
26076     if (likely(err == exc_type)) return 1;
26077     if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
26078         if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type))) {
26079             return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, NULL, exc_type);
26080         } else if (likely(PyTuple_Check(exc_type))) {
26081             return __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(err, exc_type);
26082         } else {
26083         }
26084     }
26085     return PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type);
26086 }
26087 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject *exc_type1, PyObject *exc_type2) {
26088     assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type1));
26089     assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type2));
26090     if (likely(err == exc_type1 || err == exc_type2)) return 1;
26091     if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
26092         return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, exc_type1, exc_type2);
26093     }
26094     return (PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type1) || PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type2));
26095 }
26096 #endif
26097 
26098 /* CheckBinaryVersion */
26099 static unsigned long __Pyx_get_runtime_version(void) {
26100 #if __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B00A4
26101     return Py_Version & ~0xFFUL;
26102 #else
26103     const char* rt_version = Py_GetVersion();
26104     unsigned long version = 0;
26105     unsigned long factor = 0x01000000UL;
26106     unsigned int digit = 0;
26107     int i = 0;
26108     while (factor) {
26109         while ('0' <= rt_version[i] && rt_version[i] <= '9') {
26110             digit = digit * 10 + (unsigned int) (rt_version[i] - '0');
26111             ++i;
26112         }
26113         version += factor * digit;
26114         if (rt_version[i] != '.')
26115             break;
26116         digit = 0;
26117         factor >>= 8;
26118         ++i;
26119     }
26120     return version;
26121 #endif
26122 }
26123 static int __Pyx_check_binary_version(unsigned long ct_version, unsigned long rt_version, int allow_newer) {
26124     const unsigned long MAJOR_MINOR = 0xFFFF0000UL;
26125     if ((rt_version & MAJOR_MINOR) == (ct_version & MAJOR_MINOR))
26126         return 0;
26127     if (likely(allow_newer && (rt_version & MAJOR_MINOR) > (ct_version & MAJOR_MINOR)))
26128         return 1;
26129     {
26130         char message[200];
26131         PyOS_snprintf(message, sizeof(message),
26132                       "compile time Python version %d.%d "
26133                       "of module '%.100s' "
26134                       "%s "
26135                       "runtime version %d.%d",
26136                        (int) (ct_version >> 24), (int) ((ct_version >> 16) & 0xFF),
26137                        __Pyx_MODULE_NAME,
26138                        (allow_newer) ? "was newer than" : "does not match",
26139                        (int) (rt_version >> 24), (int) ((rt_version >> 16) & 0xFF)
26140        );
26141         return PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, message, 1);
26142     }
26143 }

26145 /* InitStrings */
26146 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
26147 static int __Pyx_InitString(__Pyx_StringTabEntry t, PyObject **str) {
26148     if (t.is_unicode | t.is_str) {
26149         if (t.intern) {
26150             *str = PyUnicode_InternFromString(t.s);
26151         } else if (t.encoding) {
26152             *str = PyUnicode_Decode(t.s, t.n - 1, t.encoding, NULL);
26153         } else {
26154             *str = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(t.s, t.n - 1);
26155         }
26156     } else {
26157         *str = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(t.s, t.n - 1);
26158     }
26159     if (!*str)
26160         return -1;
26161     if (PyObject_Hash(*str) == -1)
26162         return -1;
26163     return 0;
26164 }
26165 #endif
26166 static int __Pyx_InitStrings(__Pyx_StringTabEntry *t) {
26167     while (t->p) {
26168         #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
26169         __Pyx_InitString(*t, t->p);
26170         #else
26171         if (t->is_unicode) {
26172             *t->p = PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(t->s, t->n - 1, NULL);
26173         } else if (t->intern) {
26174             *t->p = PyString_InternFromString(t->s);
26175         } else {
26176             *t->p = PyString_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
26177         }
26178         if (!*t->p)
26179             return -1;
26180         if (PyObject_Hash(*t->p) == -1)
26181             return -1;
26182         #endif
26183         ++t;
26184     }
26185     return 0;
26186 }

26189 static CYTHON_INLINE Py_ssize_t __Pyx_ssize_strlen(const char *s) {
26190     size_t len = strlen(s);
26191     if (unlikely(len > (size_t) PY_SSIZE_T_MAX)) {
26192         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError, "byte string is too long");
26193         return -1;
26194     }
26195     return (Py_ssize_t) len;
26196 }
26197 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyUnicode_FromString(const char* c_str) {
26198     Py_ssize_t len = __Pyx_ssize_strlen(c_str);
26199     if (unlikely(len < 0)) return NULL;
26200     return __Pyx_PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(c_str, len);
26201 }
26202 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyByteArray_FromString(const char* c_str) {

26207 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyObject_AsString(PyObject* o) {
26208     Py_ssize_t ignore;
26209     return __Pyx_PyObject_AsStringAndSize(o, &ignore);
26210 }
26211 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII || __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT
26212 #if !CYTHON_PEP393_ENABLED
26213 static const char* __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26214     char* defenc_c;
26215     PyObject* defenc = _PyUnicode_AsDefaultEncodedString(o, NULL);
26216     if (!defenc) return NULL;
26217     defenc_c = PyBytes_AS_STRING(defenc);
26218 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26219     {
26220         char* end = defenc_c + PyBytes_GET_SIZE(defenc);
26221         char* c;
26222         for (c = defenc_c; c < end; c++) {
26223             if ((unsigned char) (*c) >= 128) {
26224                 PyUnicode_AsASCIIString(o);
26225                 return NULL;
26226             }
26227         }
26228     }
26229 #endif
26230     *length = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(defenc);
26231     return defenc_c;
26232 }

26234 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26235     if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(o) == -1)) return NULL;
26236 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26237     if (likely(PyUnicode_IS_ASCII(o))) {
26238         *length = PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(o);
26239         return PyUnicode_AsUTF8(o);
26240     } else {
26241         PyUnicode_AsASCIIString(o);
26242         return NULL;
26243     }
26244 #else
26245     return PyUnicode_AsUTF8AndSize(o, length);
26246 #endif
26247 }
26248 #endif
26249 #endif
26250 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyObject_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26251 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII || __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT
26252     if (
26253 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3 && __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26254             __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii &&
26255 #endif
26256             PyUnicode_Check(o)) {
26257         return __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(o, length);
26258     } else
26259 #endif
26260 #if (!CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API) || (defined(PyByteArray_AS_STRING) && defined(PyByteArray_GET_SIZE))
26261     if (PyByteArray_Check(o)) {
26262         *length = PyByteArray_GET_SIZE(o);
26263         return PyByteArray_AS_STRING(o);
26264     } else
26265 #endif
26266     {
26267         char* result;
26268         int r = PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(o, &result, length);
26269         if (unlikely(r < 0)) {
26270             return NULL;
26271         } else {
26272             return result;
26273         }
26274     }
26275 }
26276 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(PyObject* x) {
26277    int is_true = x == Py_True;
26278    if (is_true | (x == Py_False) | (x == Py_None)) return is_true;
26279    else return PyObject_IsTrue(x);
26280 }
26281 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrueAndDecref(PyObject* x) {
26282     int retval;
26283     if (unlikely(!x)) return -1;
26284     retval = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(x);
26285     Py_DECREF(x);
26286     return retval;
26287 }
26288 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLongWrongResultType(PyObject* result, const char* type_name) {
26289     __Pyx_TypeName result_type_name = __Pyx_PyType_GetName(Py_TYPE(result));
26290 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
26291     if (PyLong_Check(result)) {
26292         if (PyErr_WarnFormat(PyExc_DeprecationWarning, 1,
26293                 "__int__ returned non-int (type " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME ").  "
26294                 "The ability to return an instance of a strict subclass of int is deprecated, "
26295                 "and may be removed in a future version of Python.",
26296                 result_type_name)) {
26297             __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(result_type_name);
26298             Py_DECREF(result);
26299             return NULL;
26300         }
26301         __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(result_type_name);
26302         return result;
26303     }
26304 #endif
26305     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
26306                  "__%.4s__ returned non-%.4s (type " __Pyx_FMT_TYPENAME ")",
26307                  type_name, type_name, result_type_name);
26308     __Pyx_DECREF_TypeName(result_type_name);
26309     Py_DECREF(result);
26310     return NULL;
26311 }
26312 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(PyObject* x) {
26313 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
26314   PyNumberMethods *m;
26315 #endif
26316   const char *name = NULL;
26317   PyObject *res = NULL;
26318 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26319   if (likely(PyInt_Check(x) || PyLong_Check(x)))
26320 #else
26321   if (likely(PyLong_Check(x)))
26322 #endif
26323     return __Pyx_NewRef(x);
26324 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
26325   m = Py_TYPE(x)->tp_as_number;
26326   #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26327   if (m && m->nb_int) {
26328     name = "int";
26329     res = m->nb_int(x);
26330   }
26331   else if (m && m->nb_long) {
26332     name = "long";
26333     res = m->nb_long(x);
26334   }
26335   #else
26336   if (likely(m && m->nb_int)) {
26337     name = "int";
26338     res = m->nb_int(x);
26339   }
26340   #endif
26341 #else
26342   if (!PyBytes_CheckExact(x) && !PyUnicode_CheckExact(x)) {
26343     res = PyNumber_Int(x);
26344   }
26345 #endif
26346   if (likely(res)) {
26347 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26348     if (unlikely(!PyInt_Check(res) && !PyLong_Check(res))) {
26349 #else
26350     if (unlikely(!PyLong_CheckExact(res))) {
26351 #endif
26352         return __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLongWrongResultType(res, name);
26353     }
26354   }
26355   else if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
26356     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
26357                     "an integer is required");
26358   }
26359   return res;
26360 }
26361 static CYTHON_INLINE Py_ssize_t __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(PyObject* b) {
26362   Py_ssize_t ival;
26363   PyObject *x;
26364 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26365   if (likely(PyInt_CheckExact(b))) {
26366     if (sizeof(Py_ssize_t) >= sizeof(long))
26367         return PyInt_AS_LONG(b);
26368     else
26369         return PyInt_AsSsize_t(b);
26370   }
26371 #endif
26372   if (likely(PyLong_CheckExact(b))) {
26373     #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
26374     if (likely(__Pyx_PyLong_IsCompact(b))) {
26375         return __Pyx_PyLong_CompactValue(b);
26376     } else {
26377       const digit* digits = __Pyx_PyLong_Digits(b);
26378       const Py_ssize_t size = __Pyx_PyLong_SignedDigitCount(b);
26379       switch (size) {
26380          case 2:
26381            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26382              return (Py_ssize_t) (((((size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26383            }
26384            break;
26385          case -2:
26386            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26387              return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26388            }
26389            break;
26390          case 3:
26391            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26392              return (Py_ssize_t) (((((((size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26393            }
26394            break;
26395          case -3:
26396            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26397              return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((((size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26398            }
26399            break;
26400          case 4:
26401            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26402              return (Py_ssize_t) (((((((((size_t)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26403            }
26404            break;
26405          case -4:
26406            if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26407              return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((((((size_t)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26408            }
26409            break;
26410       }
26411     }
26412     #endif
26413     return PyLong_AsSsize_t(b);
26414   }
26415   x = PyNumber_Index(b);
26416   if (!x) return -1;
26417   ival = PyInt_AsSsize_t(x);
26418   Py_DECREF(x);
26419   return ival;
26420 }
26421 static CYTHON_INLINE Py_hash_t __Pyx_PyIndex_AsHash_t(PyObject* o) {
26422   if (sizeof(Py_hash_t) == sizeof(Py_ssize_t)) {
26423     return (Py_hash_t) __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(o);
26424 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26425   } else if (likely(PyInt_CheckExact(o))) {
26426     return PyInt_AS_LONG(o);
26427 #endif
26428   } else {
26429     Py_ssize_t ival;
26430     PyObject *x;
26431     x = PyNumber_Index(o);
26432     if (!x) return -1;
26433     ival = PyInt_AsLong(x);
26434     Py_DECREF(x);
26435     return ival;
26436   }
26437 }
26438 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyBool_FromLong(long b) {
26439   return b ? __Pyx_NewRef(Py_True) : __Pyx_NewRef(Py_False);
26440 }
26441 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyInt_FromSize_t(size_t ival) {
26442     return PyInt_FromSize_t(ival);
26443 }
